beers.desc: Smells hoppy but tastes stouty

beers.name: Akasha fire within
beers.desc: Pretty spot on for what I expect from an amber ale but doesn't have a flavour I love

beers.name: Derwent aromatic spelt ale
beers.desc: Only slightly sour and it all comes together well. It's not a style that I'm used to but I do enjoy it

beers.name: Grifter Serpents kiss
beers.desc: The slight watermelon taste makes it hard to enjoy the beer. You get used to it but there's not a lot of reason to

beers.name: Dark knight porter style
beers.desc: Mild and sweet. Nice easy drinking porter

beers.name: Feral karma citra
beers.desc: A little bit too stouty and bitter for me but otherwise good

beers.name: Moo brew single hop
beers.desc: A little bit lacking on the hop side but well rounded. Kind of want to know what hop and malt they use

beers.name: Brabante lager
beers.desc: Pretty plain lager, slightly better than your standard Australian beers

beers.name: Stone IPA
beers.desc: Very bitter and lacking in hops but ok

beers.name: Akasha water buffalo
beers.desc: Has a few flavours which are hard to pin down but it works well. Has a nice amount of sweetness

beers.name: Arc Valley Lager
beers.desc: Nothing particularly good about this beer. It’s drinkable but that’s about it

beers.name: Namysrów pils
beers.desc: Malty European pils. Nothing special

beers.name: Sierra Nevada Otra vez
beers.desc: Smells strange bad but tastes completely different. Having trouble describing exactly what I’m getting here, kind of like watermelon. Perhaps too many things going on all at once. I wouldn’t want many but it’s worth the experience

beers.name: Magic rock Cannonball IPA
beers.desc: Has the floral smell that I love in an IPA and a nice balance of bitterness and hops. A great example of an IPA

beers.name: Exit milk stout
beers.desc: Not nearly as sweet as I expected, almost had a sour note. Once I got used to it it was an enjoyable drink

beers.name: The continuous daryl
beers.desc: One amazing beer. Spot on with bitterness and fruitiness

beers.name: Holgate temptress
beers.desc: A little bit too bitter and too stouty for me. Not getting any chocolate either

beers.name: Magic rock high wire grapefruit
beers.desc: Fruity like a soft drink but still bitter like a beer. Smells a little bit like past. Different and refreshing

beers.name: Holgate hop tart
beers.desc: An interesting beer. Could do with a little more hop flavour to go with the sourness but refreshing as it is

beers.name: Rogue dead guy
beers.desc: Like a really sweet IPA. There’s something else in there that I can’t put my finger on

beers.name: Skorubrew #6
beers.desc: A little underwhelmed with the hop flavour, it didn’t come out as strong as I expected. While I wouldn’t really call this an IPA it’s still a nice beer. Not too bitter and really easy to drink

beers.name: Magic rock salty kiss
beers.desc: Fairly mild on flavour. Easy to drink and refreshing

beers.name: Tuatara outrigger
beers.desc: More of a Belgian flavour than I expected. Ok but not great

beers.name: Legal tender
beers.desc: Has a slightly sweet taste and a spicy finish. Drink it quick before it gets warm

beers.name: Lord Nelson dead ahead
beers.desc: There's an interesting background flavour, perhaps honey, but it's overwhelmed by the bitterness. A little disappointing

beers.name: Skorubrew #5
beers.desc: Definitely tastes like a belgian ale. Not the favourite beer I've made but it's ok

beers.name: Skorubrew #7
beers.desc: There’s a slight caramel/toffee flavour that comes through but the apple isn’t there except for the smell. More bitter than my other beers but it’s not overwhelming

beers.name: Skorubrew #8
beers.desc: A much more in your face stout than my #3. The chocolate hasn’t come through but the sweetness from the lactose has. There’s a noticeable coffee flavour as well that I didn’t expect. Amazingly though it comes together really well and is quite easy drinking

beers.name: Six strings dark red IPA
beers.desc: Too much bitterness overwhelming the other flavours

beers.name: Cleanskin Green beer
beers.desc: Not as cheap tasting as I expected. Low bitterness and a sweet malt profile make it fairly drinkable

beers.name: Yenda Hell
beers.desc: Almost tasteless. Absolutely nothing exciting about this beer

beers.name: Barossa brewing I can't believe it's not bacon
beers.desc: Super smokey but not overwhelming. Definitely evokes memories of bacon

beers.name: West end draught
beers.desc: Uninspired south Australian lager. Not as bitter as other Australian brews but there's no hops or malt to make it s decent beer

beers.name: Barossa valley SA wit
beers.desc: Really refreshing. Would go great on a hot day. One of the better wit beers I've had

beers.name: Clare valley bulls eye
beers.desc: Overly bitter with no hop profile

beers.name: Prancing pony sunshine ale
beers.desc: A little bit lacking but not a bad beer

beers.name: Clare valley monkey's uncle
beers.desc: Another bitter beer but tastes like a red ale. Decent flavours behind the bitterness

beers.name: Malt fiction session ale
beers.desc: Very easy drinking. Not a lot of flavour but for something you’re drinking all day this would be great. A little bit tangy

beers.name: Magic hat smash hits IPA
beers.desc: Definitely an IPA but not terribly nice. Surprisingly the bitterness went away as it got warmer and it was a bit nicer

beers.name: Magic hat Stealin time
beers.desc: Really nice ginger hit

beers.name: Mornington dogs bollocks
beers.desc: Oh so smooth. One of easiest drinking beers I’ve ever had

beers.name: Innes & Gunn fired oak scotch ale
beers.desc: You can really taste the oak flavours coming through Has a slightly strange flavour but overall pretty nice

beers.name: James squire hop thief #8
beers.desc: Didn’t think I would enjoy this one as much as the #7 given the hops but it’s just as good

beers.name: Steam whistle pilsner
beers.desc: Easy drinking. Fairly dry and not too bitter

beers.name: Mismatch Extra pale ale
beers.desc: Really tasty brew. Not as bitter as I expected which works well with mild hop flavour

beers.name: Shark island pale ale
beers.desc: My first from this brewery, happy so far. Mild on hops but the sweetness from the malt holds it together

beers.name: Shark island summer ale
beers.desc: A little bit too yeasty. Not what I expect from a summer ale

beers.name: Blackfont Belgian pale ale
beers.desc: Perfect example of a Belgian

beers.name: Blackfont saison de Ville
beers.desc: The best saison I've had. Like drinking a piece of fruit

beers.name: Batch juicy as phuck dark
beers.desc: So much hop aroma with no bitterness. A style I've been searching for but it could be more balanced

beers.name: Batch tank 6 imperial stout
beers.desc: There's a beautiful flavour but it's hidden behind some harshness which slightly spoils it

beers.name: Feral smoked porter
beers.desc: Smooth but without the backing to make it a great beer

beers.name: Hotchkiss six
beers.desc: Really mild easy drinking stout. Kind of lacks any interesting depth of flavour

beers.name: Anderson valley blood orange gose
beers.desc: Takes a bit of getting used to, orange doesn’t usually go with salty. Not something I would buy again

beers.name: Redbay bearded hobo pale ale
beers.desc: Crisp and dry. Very easy drinking, a great pale ale for someone new to beer

beers.name: Redbay Vlad White IPA
beers.desc: The hops cut through what I normally dislike in a wheat beer. Nicely aromatic and not too bitter

beers.name: Redbay Black gold coffee porter
beers.desc: A nice balance between beer and coffee. Could do with some more sweetness

beers.name: Liebenweiss hefe weissbier
beers.desc: Really citrusy which hides the yeastiness

beers.name: Destroy all humans
beers.desc: Tastes like it wants to kill me. Was this even supposed to be consumed?

beers.name: Willie smith triple
beers.desc: Super strange color but with an amazing taste. Starts with a kick then followed by a mild berry sweetness which then mellows out for a smooth finish

beers.name: Anderson Valley Hop Ottin IPA
beers.desc: Super flavourful. Initially it’s very bitter but once you get over that it’s amazing. It’s exactly what I expect when a beer says it’s an IPA. Not to mention it just looks beautiful in a glass. If you see it try it out

beers.name: Merchant Hasselsloth west coast IPA
beers.desc: After the IPA I just had this seems a bit tasteless. It’s not bad in any way it’s just that I had already been spoiled somewhat during the evening. The name is of course what drew me in and can’t be faulted but the beer isn’t as flavourful as I would like

beers.name: Little brewing death between the tanks DIPA
beers.desc: After having 2 IPAs this was the perfect follow on. My palate was fully ready to ignore the 113 IBUs and delve into the flavours beneath. It’s full of citrusy hops which give you fruitiness but with the undeniable awareness that this is a strong beer. As I finish my glass I look at the bottom with sadness that I have no more of this supreme liquid, I’m left only with the hoppy smell of the bottle and the realisation that the next beer will not be as good

beers.name: Magic hat poppy agave ale
beers.desc: Not terribly exciting. The agave seems to smooth it out a bit but not enough to really differentiate it

beers.name: Basement brew house American pale ale
beers.desc: Has a nice balance between IPA bitterness and the easy drinking of a pale. It's not special but it's a crowd pleaser

beers.name: Basement brew house sparkling
beers.desc: Strong on galaxy hops, low on bitterness. Really easy drinking but in no way plain

beers.name: Yulli's fat nerd vanilla porter
beers.desc: No question of the vanilla. The sweetness makes it a really nice porter but by the end of a pint it felt like a bit much. Would only recommend ordering a middy

beers.name: Wayward Keller instinct
beers.desc: Has a really strange flavour in the back. Interesting as something I've not had before but not going to bring me back

beers.name: White rabbit barrel aged red
beers.desc: An interesting style. Kind of a half sour beer.  Hints of cherry. Worth a look if you want something new

beers.name: Brewcult get down American brown
beers.desc: More of a stout than a brown due to the lack of sweetness. Kind of disappointing

beers.name: Wayward Pine-a-pils
beers.desc: Nice hoppiness but theres a harshness to it that detracts a little bit

beers.name: Wayward smokin aces
beers.desc: The smokiness enhances the bitterness without adding much

beers.name: Wayward saison
beers.desc: Nice level of yeast flavour vs sweetness. Makes me not hate saisons

beers.name: Wayward  fusami
beers.desc: Ok, but a little mild. For some reason I thought it was an IPA not a lager

beers.name: Stone & wood garden ale
beers.desc: A little lacking in flavour but easily drinkable

beers.name: 4 pines hoppy dobblebock
beers.desc: Not really my cup of tea. The flavours just don’t seem to work well together

beers.name: Phoenix beer
beers.desc: Quite a dry beer. Nothing exciting or worth looking for

beers.name: Brewdog Jet Black Heart
beers.desc: Reminds me of drinking in Shoreditch. Initially lots of coffee and chocolate but then a slight milkiness. Easy drinking and also lots of flavour

beers.name: FoxHat metric IPA
beers.desc: Given the 80 IBU it’s amazing how smooth and easy drinking this beer is. Great to see a west coast IPA which strives for balance over just packing in hops

beers.name: Brewdog Ace of Simcoe
beers.desc: I love the smell and the floral side of the hops but there’s a harsh bitterness that’s out of place. It’s a decent IPA but there’s nothing amazing going on

beers.name: Boatrocker hop bomb IPA
beers.desc: Definitely a lot of hops but the heavy use of earthy hops leaves it bitter but without any exciting flavours. My first from this brewery so hopefully the rest of their range is a bit better

beers.name: Skorubrew #13 rice ale
beers.desc: Smells citrusy and yeasty, the yeasty smell probably being the biggest let down. Has a sweet and very mild taste. A very refreshing and easy drinking beer. Also it just look beautiful

beers.name: Oskar blues pinner
beers.desc: Amazingly crisp smell of passionfruit coming through. Doesn’t carry through as much in the taste but it’s still there. There’s a bitterness too but it’s nicely balanced and overall delicious. This beer delivers everything it says on the can

beers.name: Skorubrew #9 Pale ale
beers.desc: A little over carbonated with no head retention but still a tasty drop. Fairly easy drinking with just a mild hop flavour. Has a sweet finish that takes away the bitterness

beers.name: Boatrocker tripel
beers.desc: Has a lovely nice yeasty aroma. There’s a rich warming sensation as you drink combined with a rich full flavour that is exactly what I expect from a tripel. Absolutely no harshness despite the high percentage and barely any perceptible bitterness

beers.name: Mornington hop culture
beers.desc: Lots of flavour given that it’s a session IPA. Seemed a little too bitter at first but once you get used to that it’s easy drinking. More earthy than floral but well balanced

beers.name: Welders dog IPA
beers.desc: Can’t say I really enjoyed this one

beers.name: Quiet deeds pale ale
beers.desc: Fairly bitter for a pale but not too much and still easy drinking . Light fruity smell and a dark orange colour. Continues to get better as it goes down

beers.name: Shenanigans malt assault
beers.desc: One of the better smoked beers that I've had due. From the first sip one of the strangest beers I've had but it definitely got better. By the end the smokiness was less evident and I could enjoy the multitude of other flavours

beers.name: Brewdog elvis juice
beers.desc: The flavours aren't quite coming together on this one. The smell works but there's just too much bitterness from the grapefruit

beers.name: Fox hat lusty lager
beers.desc: Like taking a regular lager and boosting it in every way. Stronger, more flavour and less harshness. Good for enjoying at a moderate pace

beers.name: Nomad freshie salt & pepper
beers.desc: One of the better beers from nomad. Just a slight saltiness but mostly just a refreshing beer

beers.name: Fix
beers.desc: Better than expected. Has that malty Eastern European taste but there’s a little bit of a tang which rounds it off nicely

beers.name: Willie the boatman nectar of the hops
beers.desc: Just the beer I've been looking for. Barely any bitterness but full of hop flavours. Smell is all pine and floral. Not getting the juiciness promised but decent as an IPA

beers.name: Skorubrew #14 belgian apple ale
beers.desc: Really rounded flavour. Much less hoppy than my other brews and the slight apple tang adds something that you wouldn’t normally see. The high ABV adds another element. Overall a decent and unique beer

beers.name: Big wave golden ale
beers.desc: Very refreshing. Has a slight creaminess

beers.name: 4 pines Indian summer ale
beers.desc: Refreshing and easy drinking. Low bitterness, not much in the way of hops but enough to make it tasty

beers.name: Akasha Korban DIPA
beers.desc: It's what it says it is so I can't complain but there's a mildness that leaves me wanting.  Neither a great hop profile nor a punch in the face. Perhaps if I got a pint it would have been better

beers.name: Golden road gingerbread stout
beers.desc: You can really taste the gingerbread. There's also a lot of stoutiness. Can't say I would buy another but it's very interesting

beers.name: Pirate life golden era
beers.desc: Nicely aromatic. Easy drinking. The mildest beer I've had from the pirate life range

beers.name: Alesmith IPA
beers.desc: Has a bitterness that never really resolves into a great flavour

beers.name: Hope black IPA
beers.desc: Not too bad. The bitterness sits well with the slight stoutiness

beers.name: Fixation IPA
beers.desc: Really floral hop profile. Not nearly as big as I expected from the description but it's a nice balance that I could drink a few of

beers.name: Boatrocker alpha queen
beers.desc: Kind of a mix between an IPA and a pale. Low on bitterness but high on hops. Great as a session beer

beers.name: Imperial
beers.desc: Fairly plain lager. I don't want another

beers.name: Mornington porter
beers.desc: A good beer to enjoy slowly. Unmistakably a porter but it all fits together well

beers.name: Rochefort 10
beers.desc: It's been a while since I've had a beer that takes so long to get used to but continues to get better. Still can't say I love it but I would love to have more to continue to tease out the flavours

beers.name: Westmalle triple
beers.desc: Pretty good tipple this triple is. Easy drinking, nice and rounded. Slight spiciness. All the things I love

beers.name: Devils daughters
beers.desc: Decent aroma but lacks flavour. Doesn't qualify as a double IPA but still decent. Too many cheap hops I think

beers.name: Katoomba brewing great white fleet
beers.desc: Not the greatest pale. Just not the hops for me. But it's not offensive

beers.name: Spiced pumpkin ale
beers.desc: Has the pumpkin spice taste but the aftertaste has something confusing that slightly ruins it

beers.name: Fox hat phat mongrel
beers.desc: Low bitterness and the oats add a lot of smoothness. Worth trying even if you're not a fan of stouts. As it goes down the creaminess becomes more evident

beers.name: Feral war hog
beers.desc: Really nice smell and color but the taste doesn't meet my expectations. Too resiny and bitter. Gets better but it's too late

beers.name: Modus operandi sonic prayer
beers.desc: Surprisingly low of aroma but big on taste. Bitter to start but great to finish. Need to get more into this brewery

beers.name: 4 pines guava gose
beers.desc: Perfectly on par with what I expect. Salty and sour with some lingering flavour.  Not a great refreshing summer beer but good as a slow drink

beers.name: Oskar blues IPA
beers.desc: Pretty good piney kind of IPA. No depth to it though

beers.name: Skorubrew #16
beers.desc: Very much a Belgian ale. Not too bitter and very low on hop flavour. Not very pretty. Probably a good winter beer, sadly I brewed it in the summer

beers.name: AC/DC Premium Lager
beers.desc: A fairly plain and easy drinking beer. Giving it an extra point because of the sheer size of it. Managed to get through the whole thing in one sitting

beers.name: DAX
beers.desc: A little malty but really low compared to other euro lagers. Mostly just tastes like water

beers.name: Nomad long reef pale ale
beers.desc: Too bitter for a pale ale. It's decently balanced but the hop profile is a bit bland

beers.name: Anderson valley holy gose
beers.desc: Perfectly balances the salt,sour and sweetness to hit that gose sweet spot. Unfortunately I was in a bit of a rush so I had to slam this down, and while it is refreshing it also has enough flavour to make that difficult so I may have enjoyed this less than I could have

beers.name: Mornington lager
beers.desc: Very easy drinking. Would be great for getting pissed. Can't complain

beers.name: Shenanigans gone troppo
beers.desc: Tropical smell but not too strong. They've managed to get a lot of tropical flavour in there as well. Still had the bitterness of an IPA but it's not overwhelming. All round a delicious beer that delivers what it promises

beers.name: Stockade wanderer märzen
beers.desc: Strange and a little tangy. Smells a bit sour. Very little hop flavour or aroma, kind of sits in an odd spot between quaffable and flavourful brews. Pretty good with food

beers.name: XXXX summer bright lager
beers.desc: As it warms up it gets a real wheaty malt flavour. Mostly just a plain lager

beers.name: Coopers limited edition brew A, IPA
beers.desc: Pretty flavourless IPA. Was expecting more from coopers

beers.name: Liberty brewing citra DIPA
beers.desc: Has a really strange tang, not bad, just unexpected. Probably a tad too bitter for the amount of flavour packed in. Could be that I just ate a steak and a whole cob loaf and didn't have the space in my stomach left

beers.name: Hawkers IPA
beers.desc: Fairly well rounded, not too bitter. Easy drinking for an IPA and the ABV. More pine than floral with the hops but it woks well

beers.name: Baladin Isaac
beers.desc: One of the better wheat ales I've had. Almost no bitterness, really refreshing and just a little bit sweet. The wheat flavour is clearly there but not bothering me

beers.name: Fox hat red pelt
beers.desc: Feels like it's missing something. The bitterness is there but sadly no great flavour behind that. Really high levels of sediment as well. A rare miss from fox hat

beers.name: Belching beaver peanut butter stout
beers.desc: Can't pick out the peanut butter but there's a great smoothness that comes with it. Kind of wish they just called it a stout and didn't get my hopes up

beers.name: Doctors orders tonic witbeer
beers.desc: Very refreshing which is exactly what I need on a 40C day. Certainly has a taste of tonic, in a good way. I'm torn between loving this as an easy drinking beer and missing more interesting flavours

beers.name: Skorubrew #18
beers.desc: Has a beautiful hazy golden color. Starts off a bit yeasty but that fades quickly. Almost no lingering bitterness and there's a slight tangy flavour but there's just too something that seems wrong

beers.name: Brewdog hop fiction pale ale
beers.desc: A tad harsh but a decent floral aroma. Just the right level of flavour for a pale ale to be interesting and easily sessionable. Sadly I only have the 1

beers.name: To Øl wit or witout
beers.desc: A balance between a wit and a sour but perhaps too bitter to sit in that range. Fairly easy drinking but not as refreshing as I was hoping. Hard to pick out any flavours

beers.name: Skorubrew #17
beers.desc: My saison dry hopped with lemon grass. Has an interesting little tang to it. Has much less of a Belgian flavour than the #16 and is more rounded. Still more of a slow drinking winter beer than a refreshing saison

beers.name: Wild yak pacific ale
beers.desc: Easy drinking but with enough flavour to keep me happy

beers.name: Koshihikari echigo
beers.desc: It's decent, slightly better than I expected. Not too much hop forward flavour. Going well with dinner

beers.name: Modus operandi session IPA
beers.desc: Sweet drinking. Probably a little bit too drunk to fully appreciate this

beers.name: Kalnapils pilsner
beers.desc: I'm hungover and right now this is a massive help. Super easy drinking and right on point for a pilsner

beers.name: Golden road wolf mother triple IPA
beers.desc: Surprisingly smooth. Not actually that bitter. It's amazing when you can knock off this amount of booze and still feel like it's a fresh beer

beers.name: Beer of the dead porter
beers.desc: A sweet smell with a mild stoutiness. Not super exciting but on point for what is and easy to drink

beers.name: Golden road saison citron
beers.desc: A little bit too heavy on the farmhouse sharpness for me

beers.name: Extra hop sauce
beers.desc: Medium bitterness and heavy on earthy hops. Good middle of the road IPA

beers.name: Young Henry's mulberia
beers.desc: Interesting colour, I expected it to be a little more sour. It's mild and easy drinking but sits in a place that's not quite my thing

beers.name: Willie the boatman salty melon
beers.desc: Once you get past the salt there's a touch of melon. The only issue is the more you drink the thirstier your get. But it delivers everything it promises

beers.name: Australian new world pilsner
beers.desc: A little too dry for my liking

beers.name: La Sirène praline
beers.desc: Like Nutella in beer form but also not at all. Nutty, chocolaty, smooth and oh so dark. Rather filling for a beer which makes me happy with one despite it being a tasty beer

beers.name: Newstead two to the valley
beers.desc: Not sure what's in this IPA but it's all wrong. Like really difficult to drink

beers.name: Beer of the dead hop on or die
beers.desc: I don’t think my cat isn’t too happy about being used as a prop. There’s a nice warmingness but it goes down pretty easy. No great hoppyness but it’s well balanced

beers.name: Stelle and Strisce
beers.desc: One of the most over carbonated beers I’ve found. Took forever for the head to reach drinkable levels. Smells of some slightly funky yeast and that carries though to the taste but the flavour is mild otherwise. It’s in a spot where it’s almost amazing but doesn’t quite manage to get there

beers.name: Buxton Pic Tor
beers.desc: Unfortunately this beer has a sourness that just tastes off. Like rotten fruit or beer mixed with shit wine

beers.name: Balter XPA
beers.desc: A nice bit of hops with low bitterness. I've never been a fan of XPAs before but I really see how this works as a style. Also the can is smiling at me

beers.name: Skorubrew #19 red rye IPA
beers.desc: A little darker than I planned but still red. Has a yeasty, Belgian smell which fades and lets the smokiness through. But the hero here is the taste. The smoked malt and rye add an element that you don’t normally find. The lower bitterness means this flavour doesn’t linger which keeps you wanting more. The Belgian yeast rounds the flavour further and the 7.5% gives a slight warming sensation. My best homebrew yet

beers.name: Wrong side brewing pale ale
beers.desc: A little biscuity but otherwise a pretty plain and tasteless beer

beers.name: Brew by numbers Belgian pale
beers.desc: Mild for a Belgian ale which makes it easy drinking but also leaves me wanting more. And I mean more in the beer, not wanting another. Not that I would complain

beers.name: Boatrocker pale ale
beers.desc: Has a weird after taste that doesn't belong in this beer. There's something interesting as well but altogether it doesn't quite work

beers.name: Batch trippy hippy citra xpa
beers.desc: Piney but lacking citrus to round it out. Gets better as I drink but it almost has a wheat flavour which I wasn't what I was hoping for

beers.name: Doctors orders saccharophobic
beers.desc: Not as much caramel as I hoped. It's definitely there but you have to search. It's an easy drinking brown with a little bit extra and I wish I had some more

beers.name: Yeastie boys bigmouth
beers.desc: Fairly sessionable but not as good as other things I've had from them. But perhaps I've just hit the point where I've had enough beer for the night

beers.name: Carling black label
beers.desc: Fairly dry with a little hint of malt in the back. A little stronger than most lagers which is nice. Easy drinking but it’s not an exciting beer

beers.name: 4 pines Keller door hop hash XPA
beers.desc: Nice selection of hops. Perhaps just a little too harsh for my liking but still easy drinking and full of flavour. Feel like I could drink a lot of these

beers.name: Pirate life white labs pilsner
beers.desc: Has a really lovely spicyness which gives this beer a little more flavour than a regular pilsner. Still easy drinking and smooth but with enough depth to keep me happy

beers.name: Viven Master IPA
beers.desc: Not really what I expect from an IPA but that’s normal for a Belgian IPA. I’m torn between this being an easy and balanced drink and it lacking exciting flavours. There’s a little bit of spiciness as it warms at least

beers.name: Castle lager
beers.desc: It’s lager. Nothing much else to say

beers.name: Newsteads wastelands red rye IPA
beers.desc: Really loving rye in beers lately where it’s not overwhelming. Because this isn’t a hoppy beer it’s still the hero

beers.name: Dam burg
beers.desc: Lager with a slightly richer level of malt than normal

beers.name: Kaiju! Hopped out red
beers.desc: Has a really deep flavour. The earthy hops are there but they don’t take away from this being a red ale. Overall it’s really well balanced and easy drinking

beers.name: Kaiju! Metamorphosis IPA
beers.desc: Too heavy on the bitterness for my liking and quite piney and resiny. Having a couple would be nice to give me more time to get used to it and pick out the hop flavours over the bitterness

beers.name: Kaiju! robohop
beers.desc: Heavy and full of flavour. Good mix of hops in the middle of floral and earthy . High starting bitterness but it doesn't linger

beers.name: La Sirène Urban Pale
beers.desc: Straight away has a saison yeasty tang. More restrained on the hops than I expected from a pale. Light, refreshing and easy to drink, just not what I expected

beers.name: Del Borgo Prunus
beers.desc: The colour is absolutely beautiful. Smells funky as hell but the taste is much better. Full of a sour fruitiness and reminds me of plums but doesn’t have any off flavours. There’s almost no bitterness and a subtle sweetness to finish

beers.name: Colonial draught Kölsch
beers.desc: A great refreshing beer. Malt driven but not to the level of European lagers. Exactly what I expect from a kölsch

beers.name: Liberty brewing yakima monster
beers.desc: Resiny and citrus hops. It could almost be an IPA given the ABV and amount of hops. Fairly well rounded overall and the more I drink the more I wish I had another one

beers.name: Ridgeway IPA
beers.desc: Has a mild Belgian yeastiness. Not at all what I expect from an IPA but it’s enjoyable nonetheless. Mild and easy drinking with a slight taste of hops

beers.name: Ballast point even keel
beers.desc: A lot of flavour for a small beer. Tastes very much like a west coast IPA. My main complaint is that while the bitterness and hops are there the mouthfeel is a bit watery so it doesn’t have the a nice smoothness. Worth a try but I wouldn’t be looking for another

beers.name: Nomad Rosie’s summer punch
beers.desc: I think this is the best berliner weisse I’ve found. Really refreshing and easy drinking with just a slight sourness

beers.name: Oskar blues beerito
beers.desc: Expected something light and tasteless. It’s actually quite malty and full of flavour. Still not exciting enough to bring me back

beers.name: Skorubrew #20 witbier
beers.desc: Love the colour I got with this one but not much else. A really yeast driven beer and perhaps too much for my taste

beers.name: Newstead 21 feet 7 inches
beers.desc: Such a smooth dark beer. Dominated by a rich coffee flavour. I don’t even like coffee but I like this. Not much malt going on. Fairly light on the sweetness but the bitterness also so that’s balances out for me

beers.name: Wrong side brewing Raspberry pale
beers.desc: Definitely has a raspberry flavour in there but fairly mild otherwise. Not sour like you might expect from a fruit beer. Interesting concept but could do with some hops to balance the sweetness

beers.name: Kaiju! crush
beers.desc: I’ve been dying to try out this beer. The hops are all floral and citrus but without any of the bitterness that normally comes with such a hoppy beer. It manages to be refreshing while still packing in tons of flavour. Reminds me a lot of the pirate life pale ale

beers.name: Big shed golden stout time
beers.desc: Smells like vanilla and cookies, so much so that the initial bitterness is a shock. Seems like an attempt to mix the flavours of an ice cream with beer, which is obviously difficult so it’s a complex beer that just manages to hold together

beers.name: Moondog splice of heaven
beers.desc: The bottle kicked off the experience by frothing all over the table. Definitely smells like lime but I can’t taste it

beers.name: Valhalla Ziggy
beers.desc: Really easy drinking for a red ale, mellow as hell. Usually I love big beers full of flavour but this is a perfect easy drinking craft beer

beers.name: Hope DIPA
beers.desc: All pine and floral on the nose. A little resiny in taste but not to the point where it overbalances the other flavours. Definitely a hop forward bitter DIPA

beers.name: Mount pleasant shake your fruity milkshake
beers.desc: Clear but full of particles. There's something odd in this beer, not bad just a flavour I can't pick out. Bitterness is completely overshadowed by the hops, just how I like my IPA

beers.name: Modus operandi pale ale
beers.desc: A little more bitter than expected. But there's a delicious sweetness that works well. It's moderately hoppy, somewhere in the middle between easy drinking and flavourful

beers.name: Bridge side cut
beers.desc: Loving the haze on this beer. Full of floral and citrus hops with a little bit of pine. It's biter but it balances perfectly. Full of flavour but I could drink a bunch of these

beers.name: Jerkface 9000
beers.desc: Not at all what I expected from something labeled as a wheat beer, more like a hoppy pale ale. But I can’t complain because it’s pretty damn good. Manages to be easy drinking at the same time. The kind of beer you could have bunch of

beers.name: Tropical torpedo
beers.desc: Starts off tropical with quite a bit of pineapple going on. But that fades and it has a bit of a Belgian spiciness which I wasn’t expecting. It’s good but I expected more

beers.name: Oskar blues death by coconut
beers.desc: Not as much coconut as I was expected from the name. I would say there’s actually more vanilla than coconut. It’s nicely smooth, but perhaps a little bit overly sweet. Interesting to try but I’m not rushing for another

beers.name: Feral brewing tusk
beers.desc: Has a bitterness but it doesn't linger at all. Lots of fresh citrus hops making this full of flavour. Would never guess this has as much alcohol as it does, it's dangerously easy to drink

beers.name: Beer creative Einstein
beers.desc: Mostly malt driven. A little bit of a roasted flavour. It's decent but not that exciting, quite easy to drink though

beers.name: Shenanigans hoppy Gonzales
beers.desc: Straight away you get the jalapeño but it's only the taste and no heat. Fairly hoppy on the nose but it's hard to pick that up in the taste

beers.name: 4 pines nitro stout
beers.desc: Looks a lot like a Guinness but it's not as dry so easier to drink. No strong flavours but a decent session beer

beers.name: Sierra Nevada Sidecar
beers.desc: Very orange in color, smells a little like an unpeeled orange but it doesn’t really carry through to the flavour. I like the idea but it doesn’t come together that well

beers.name: Four winds Nectarous
beers.desc: I can’t pick out any of the dry hop flavours but I’m ok with that because it’s a delicious sour. The kind of sour which gets it right without bothering to worry about hiding it with fruit. It’s hard to say much about this because I don’t have much to compare it to. Definitely worth a try for anyone who feels like experimenting with sours

beers.name: All star session IPA
beers.desc: A little bitter with mostly earthy hops

beers.name: Žatecky Gus
beers.desc: Your basic flavourless lager except in a giant can. Just what I need right now

beers.name: Doan amaretto
beers.desc: Quite a lot going on but it's hard to pick out. Both a little smokey and quite creamy. There's a sweetness too but it doesn't fight with the other flavours

beers.name: Feral Fanta pants
beers.desc: Finally found a beer that lets me understand the dankness of an IPA. The bitterness is high but it’s well rounded. Seems a bit like it has many different styles of hops involved which all come together to give that dank

beers.name: Dageraad Sri Lanka
beers.desc: Definitely a Belgian ale but it’s hard to say if it’s anything more

beers.name: Founders KBS
beers.desc: Super packed with flavour. The bourbon comes through as well as a huge amount of toastyness. Can't taste the booze at all. Still not worth the price

beers.name: Founders breakfast stout
beers.desc: A nice easy drinking mild stout, pretty great example of what a stout should be

beers.name: Doctors orders electrolyte serum
beers.desc: Tastes more like a wheat ale than a gose. Not bad but I wanted more

beers.name: Dos blockos fuck the rent
beers.desc: Really flavourful golden ale full of malty goodness. Not a special beer but a decent staple

beers.name: Kona pipeline
beers.desc: Slightly watered down stout. Just doesn't have the creaminess that I want right now

beers.name: Bacchus jaffacake ale
beers.desc: A fairly thin dark ale. The chocolate and orange are fairly mild. Interesting but I probably didn't need a pint

beers.name: Bacchus Lammingtonne
beers.desc: You really get lamington as you swallow just without the sweetness. Powerful but easy drinking. Could have been a bit creamier

beers.name: Bacchus hibiscus saison
beers.desc: Looks like a feminine beer but it definitely isn't. Has a very strong Belgian taste to it. The hibiscus comes through as well. Doesn't have the freshness that I expected

beers.name: Bacchus kraken IPA
beers.desc: Pretty dank and tasty. The rum comes through but it's really faint

beers.name: Bacchus sex drugs & rocky road
beers.desc: Definitely evokes memories of rocky road but the bitterness overpowers a lot of it

beers.name: Bucket boys This is rice country
beers.desc: Very light. Has almost a slight spicyness

beers.name: Grifter banshee
beers.desc: Slight toastyness. Like a very thin stout. Easy drinking but lacks depth

beers.name: Blackfont Brett fermented Belgian
beers.desc: Full Belgian flavour but a bit lighter. Has a delicious lingering taste that I can't quite describe. Absolutely smooth with almost no bitterness

beers.name: Blackfont wheat IPA
beers.desc: Wheat is there but the hops are the hero. Still fairly light for an IPA and somehow the bitterness barely comes through

beers.name: Blackfont Baltic porter
beers.desc: Creamy for a Baltic and smooth for the strength. Fairly mild in flavour but really easy to drink

beers.name: Blackfont imperial oatmeal stout
beers.desc: Smooth and creamy with no bitterness but a little sour

beers.name: Blackfont souvenir old ale
beers.desc: Everything about this beer is amazing

beers.name: Batch hopsy mozy nitro IPA
beers.desc: Love the creamyness on this beer

beers.name: Grifter demon lungs
beers.desc: It's a good level of smoke but lacks much else

beers.name: Grifter omen
beers.desc: Good stout which causes no qualms but delivers nothing special

beers.name: Grifter tavern ale
beers.desc: My favourite of the range so far. Clean and crisp

beers.name: Coal harbour Smoke & Mirrors
beers.desc: Super smokey, in fact too much for the size of the bottle. It was smooth otherwise so there wasn't much to cover the smokiness

beers.name: Mornington brain squeeze
beers.desc: Classic Mornington quality. Slightly sour and easy drinking. A good all day beverage

beers.name: Crafty dan 13 guns
beers.desc: Decent hop aroma but it doesn't come through much in the taste. Fairly smooth for an IPA but it's not enough to save it

beers.name: Goose island 312 urban wheat ale
beers.desc: Mild in all possible ways but well balanced. The wheat is barely noticeable to the point where you could mistake this for a lager

beers.name: Under current oatmeal pale ale
beers.desc: Quite flavourful and full of hops. I like the haze but I wish it was a little creamier. Pretty good but misses its potential

beers.name: Blue point toasted lager
beers.desc: Fairly mild lager but with a little bit of something extra. Could be called an amber ale. Pretty solid all round

beers.name: The kernel Loral IPA
beers.desc: It's a strange hop. Kind of a pine and floral mix and something else I can't pinpoint

beers.name: Goose IPA
beers.desc: Fairly plain. A little too bitter for the hop level

beers.name: The kernel centennial IPA
beers.desc: It's a very ugly looking IPA. Initially very bitter but that faded. Mostly pine aroma but not much hop flavour coming through. It’s a decent IPA but doesn’t go further than that

beers.name: The kernel simcoe pale ale
beers.desc: Another fairly ugly beer, which may be the result of it being badly stored. On the nose it’s mostly citrus with a bit of spice. Full of flavour without being too bitter. Quality all round

beers.name: Sadlers Land of liberty American IPA
beers.desc: Looks and tastes nothing like an IPA. It somehow manages to be malt driven rather than hop driven. It’s not a bad beer but a complete fail for the style

beers.name: Wimbledon copper leaf ale
beers.desc: A rather mild real ale. Easy drinking but ultimately lacking flavour

beers.name: Guinness hop house 13
beers.desc: A nice hoppy lager. If you want a base lager with that little bit extra

beers.name: Meantime pale ale
beers.desc: Really nice sweetness balanced with the hops. But seems like it is more of an amber than a pale

beers.name: Maes pils
beers.desc: Pretty easy drinking, what you would expect from a pilsner

beers.name: Blanche de Brugs
beers.desc: Bang on for a witbeer. Starts out yeasty buy the lemon cuts through it. Really easy drinking and refreshing

beers.name: Delirium red
beers.desc: Expected an amber ale but got a cherry beer. Very easy drinking and refreshing without the fruit being too strong

beers.name: Bersalis triple
beers.desc: It's good but something just seems off about it. Gets better with time but never what I'm hoping for

beers.name: Grimbergen triple
beers.desc: A fairly light triple but the yeast just seems a bit off

beers.name: Kasteel rouge
beers.desc: Another cherry beer. Really need to learn what to expect from a rouge beer

beers.name: Brussels beer project delta IPA
beers.desc: The first Belgian IPA I’ve found that actually resembles an IPA. Not too bitter and moderately hoppy

beers.name: Cantillon gueuze
beers.desc: It's not as sour as I expected. Lots of really subtle flavours that take a while to get used to but it's an interesting experience

beers.name: Cantillon lambic
beers.desc: Flat and rather mild. Feels like a really old style that's hard to compare to normal beers. It's pleasant but not exciting

beers.name: Vieux temps
beers.desc: Easy drinking Belgian blonde with a slight malty finish

beers.name: Westvleteren 12
beers.desc: Really full of flavour. It's not harsh on the throat but gives a warming sensation. It's slightly tangy with a lot of candied sugar coming through. It's definitely a sipping beer but it's one you could stay on until you collapsed

beers.name: Hopus
beers.desc: Light and sweet with a mild yeastiness. Tastes like a session beer but packed with alcohol

beers.name: Trappist Achel
beers.desc: Comes off a little harsh. Ok but there are plenty of better Belgian beers

beers.name: Sion kölsch
beers.desc: Malty, low on bitterness and easy drinking. Even Amy had one

beers.name: Peters kölsch
beers.desc: A little malty with a sweet finish. Very easy to go through but not exciting

beers.name: Gaffel kölsch
beers.desc: At first it seems like the malt is overwhelming but it's hiding a hint of spice

beers.name: Jaws nuclear laundry
beers.desc: Pretty decent hop punch with a nice dankness. Surprisingly easy to drink despite this

beers.name: Stone xocoveza
beers.desc: Has a very strange taste. Apart from the bitterness it’s not much like a beer at all. It’s pretty good but not something I would go back for

beers.name: Heiden Peters DIPA
beers.desc: Absolutely amazing DIPA. Really well balanced. Hard to pick out the hop type as it seems like there’s a lot mixed in there

beers.name: Fabrik Wedding pale ale
beers.desc: A bit hoppy, a bit tangy. Rather nice all round

beers.name: Fabrik Pale ale
beers.desc: A little bitter and has a strange smell and after taste but overall pretty good

beers.name: Lübzer pils
beers.desc: A little bitter and malty but lacking any real flavour. Not something you want more of

beers.name: Berliner Marcus bräu red
beers.desc: A little tangy, seems like a mix between a pilsner and a gose. Not something I would rave about, but decent

beers.name: Berliner pilsner
beers.desc: A little harsh to start but not too bad

beers.name: Flensburger
beers.desc: Pretty easy to get down. Decent session beer

beers.name: Perlenbacher pils
beers.desc: Cheap and malty. You can't really complain at 29¢ a can

beers.name: Hafferöder premium pils
beers.desc: Not exactly premium but not awful

beers.name: Cannabis beer
beers.desc: Really weird flavour, kind of like a sour gummy worm mixed with beer

beers.name: Clock American red IPA
beers.desc: Such a great hop aroma. Much milder on the palette but well balanced. Wouldn't be upset with a few of these

beers.name: Sibeeria Baltic porter
beers.desc: Damn this is good. So rich with a slight nuttiness. A little smokey too

beers.name: Koala 12
beers.desc: Really mild lager, just a little malty

beers.name: Kozel dark unfiltered
beers.desc: Mild in flavour and quite easy drinking. A little sweet but not malty. Not what you would expect from a dark beer

beers.name: Excelent
beers.desc: Not so excellent. Fairly dry and average

beers.name: Radegast 12
beers.desc: Your basic lager

beers.name: Gösser märzen
beers.desc: Another fairly plain lager. Goes down easy though

beers.name: Ottakringer
beers.desc: Very light lager

beers.name: Ottakringer gold fassl
beers.desc: Sweet and a little malty

beers.name: Stiegl Columbus
beers.desc: Surprising hoppy for an Austrian beer. High quality beer

beers.name: Schwechater bier
beers.desc: Another plain Austrian lager. A little sweet and otherwise flavourless

beers.name: Loser bier
beers.desc: More malty than I expected. It's ok but nothing to write home about

beers.name: Hallstatt Das bier
beers.desc: Really smooth but mostly flavourless

beers.name: Eggenberg märzen
beers.desc: A little malty and not too bitter. Sessionable

beers.name: Hallstättersee bier
beers.desc: Very plain beer

beers.name: Zipfer
beers.desc: A very thin lager

beers.name: Edelweiss Dunkel
beers.desc: Absolutely awesome compared to the lagers I've been having. Full of wheat and yeast but with a smooth mouthfeel

beers.name: Egger Märzenbier
beers.desc: Just a regular lager

beers.name: Stiegl Weiss
beers.desc: A great smooth weissbier with a mild yeastiness

beers.name: Franziskaner weissbier
beers.desc: The first time I had this it was mixed with orange and lemonade, it was still good but not what I wanted. The second time it was plain which I prefer. Decent all round weissbier

beers.name: Hofbräu kaltenhausen
beers.desc: Mild and well rounded lager

beers.name: Konig Ludwig dunkel
beers.desc: Has a strange metallic taste to it. There is a slight stoutiness but it's hard to pick

beers.name: Augustiner märzen
beers.desc: Surprisingly good. A little sweet but it's subtle and the beer is so well rounded that it's done before you know it

beers.name: Castello
beers.desc: Really good summer beer. Light and easy drinking

beers.name: Bradipa
beers.desc: Misses out on any big hop flavours but isn't too bitter. A fairly relaxed IPA

beers.name: Grimbergen Blanche
beers.desc: Easy drinking and mild yet yeasty Belgian ale

beers.name: Grimbergen double
beers.desc: Can really taste the candi sugar. Nicely sweet with no bitterness. Surprisingly easy to drink

beers.name: Martens gold
beers.desc: Mild and refreshing

beers.name: Affen könig imperial IPA
beers.desc: Very floral aroma and rather bitter taste. Could be a little better balanced and have some more hop flavours

beers.name: Birra motetti grand cru
beers.desc: Very Belgian tasting. Probably a little too harsh without having any great flavours

beers.name: Bierschmiede zunder
beers.desc: Really smokey flavour and even more smell. Pretty easy drinking but no other strong flavours

beers.name: Rieder bock
beers.desc: A little yeasty and easy drinking

beers.name: Ichnusa
beers.desc: Pretty smooth lager. Something just seems wrong with it

beers.name: Baladin birra nazionale
beers.desc: Yeasty and refreshing. The flavour tends to linger a little but there's something to this that really elevates it. Nice amount of fizz

beers.name: Era ottanta tre
beers.desc: Strangely good. Just that little bit of maltiness which balances out well. The kind of drink you could smash down without realising the strength

beers.name: Fahnen bräu
beers.desc: Basic easy drinking beer

beers.name: Proper job
beers.desc: Such a great smell. Taste is pretty amazing as well. Basically your perfect fruity pale ale. Delicious to the last drop

beers.name: Goslar 1826
beers.desc: That amazing salty refreshingness. No lingering harshness but with a slight saltiness left on your lips

beers.name: Lambrate hazelnut porter
beers.desc: Hazelnut is an amazing flavour that works without sweetness. Gives you exactly what you so for

beers.name: Extraomes quadruple
beers.desc: A really bad example of a quad. The sourness becomes slightly offensive and makes it hard to get through

beers.name: Dolomiti pils
beers.desc: Mild maltiness. Pretty refreshing and easy to drink

beers.name: Birra nova margose
beers.desc: Interesting balance. More salty than sour. Not as refreshing as I hoped

beers.name: Bevog IPA
beers.desc: Smells slightly spicy and earthy. Too bitter considering the lack of hop flavours

beers.name: Gold stern
beers.desc: Pretty plain lager

beers.name: Oettinger weissbier
beers.desc: A very mild weissbier that works well. Much better than the plain one

beers.name: Lucifer
beers.desc: Little bit of a metallic taste and a cheap harshness

beers.name: Nastro azzurro
beers.desc: Golden color with a crisp refreshing taste and nice level of fizz. Great on a hot Italian day. No good once warm

beers.name: Williamsbrau pils
beers.desc: Very mild, almost water beer. Good for a cheap easy drinking beer

beers.name: Ceres Top Pilsner
beers.desc: Pretty plain lager

beers.name: Birra Dana
beers.desc: Cheap boring lager

beers.name: Hawke's lager
beers.desc: Slightly tangy lager. The name is cool but it’s overpriced for what it is

beers.name: Rocks conviction IPA
beers.desc: Nice bit of dankness and a little bit of fruit. Very little harsh bitterness. Never really gets better from the first sip

beers.name: Valhalla obsidian
beers.desc: Slightly harsh burnt coffee taste

beers.name: Sierra Nevada beer camp 2017 golden IPA
beers.desc: A very refreshing IPA. Slightly floral and very low on bitterness

beers.name: Tumut river squealing pig APA
beers.desc: Took forever for the head to settle. Smelled a little sour but doesn’t have much in the flavour

beers.name: Tree Brewing Thirsty beaver
beers.desc: Fairly on point for style. No exciting flavours going on though

beers.name: Magic rock inhaler
beers.desc: Not really juicy, more tastes like there’s a little bit of fruit juice behind the bitterness. Doesn’t really work well together. Gets better towards the end but misses the mark

beers.name: Tumut river portstar
beers.desc: Pretty well balanced with a nice sweetness. Only a little smokey

beers.name: Tumut river pale ale
beers.desc: Slightly tangy pale ale. Doesn't really have the level of hops I hoped for

beers.name: Pirate life transpacific pale ale
beers.desc: More bitter than you would expect from a pale but nicely hoppy

beers.name: Brewhouse IPA
beers.desc: Milder than expected and a little watery for an IPA. Not too bad

beers.name: Tumut river blonde
beers.desc: Nice slightly Belgian ale. Pretty easy drinking

beers.name: Southern tier 2XSMASH
beers.desc: Very little aroma but a nice bit of hops on the tongue. The bitterness overwhelms the earthy and floral hops a little bit but not too much. Would be happy with another

beers.name: Hop nation mango gose
beers.desc: Really strong mango smell and an interesting mix of flavours. The mango doesn’t come through as much in the taste as the mild sourness covers it up. Very easy drinking regardless and gets better as it goes down

beers.name: Baird Beer
beers.desc: Hard to pick what’s going on but it works well. Easy drinking and definitely a well crafted beer

beers.name: Kloud
beers.desc: Just a little malty but mostly easy drinking. More interesting than expected

beers.name: Castle milk stout
beers.desc: Quite milky and without much bitterness or harshness. Not what I expected from a mass market beer. A little thin but otherwise no complaints

beers.name: Pacific pilsner
beers.desc: Very dry. Tastes like a mainstream Australian lager

beers.name: Hargreaves cherry harvest 2016
beers.desc: Really lovely pale orange/peach colouring. Rather sour but balances out well with the other flavours. Not what you would expect from a beer but bang on for a sour

beers.name: Victory Prima pils
beers.desc: This beer really blew me away. It’s not that it’s the best but I was not expecting it to pack in the flavour that it does. So much sweetness without that cheap malty taste that you get in most pilsners. Gets a little bitter if it sits for too long but otherwise nothing wrong

beers.name: Sauce pale ale
beers.desc: A little bitter to start but that fades away. Kind of lacks the hops you would expect from a pale ale

beers.name: Blizzard Bladerunner
beers.desc: Fairly mild on the Belgian flavours which lets some more hops come through. Solid beer all the way and well rounded

beers.name: Tumut river ginja ninja
beers.desc: A little bit overly sweet

beers.name: Jacks abby calyptra
beers.desc: I was sceptical of the concept of an IPL but it has some decent piney hops coming through. Easy drinking but packed with flavour

beers.name: Akasha hopsmith IPA
beers.desc: Decent IPA. Not much aroma and a little bitter to start but finishes off nicely

beers.name: Akasha black IPA
beers.desc: Really nice mix between stout and IPA. Just a little taste of hops after the stoutiness subsides

beers.name: Akasha American stout
beers.desc: Solid stout with a little bit of coffee. Love the creamy head but that doesn't carry through to the liquid

beers.name: Deep creek pontoon in a monsoon IPA
beers.desc: A bit of a dank IPA. Decent hops and not too bitter. Very enjoyable

beers.name: Moon dog Mack daddy
beers.desc: Comes off almost sour outside the stout flavour. Drinkable but kind of thin, only bought it for the name

beers.name: Exit IPA
beers.desc: A little dank, a little floral. Not too bitter and very well balanced

beers.name: Dad and Dave’s Gold #4
beers.desc: A little bit of a European malt profile with a hint of hops. Fairly easy drinking but not too exciting

beers.name: Balter alt brown
beers.desc: A nice sweet maltiness. Not that much else going on but pleasantly easy drinking

beers.name: Aecht Schelnkerla Rauchbier
beers.desc: Love the smokey flavours coming through, almost like bacon. Tastes a little stronger than it is

beers.name: Nomad jet lag IPA
beers.desc: A little floral on the nose but mostly bitter to taste. Ok but not exciting

beers.name: Brewhouse brown ale
beers.desc: Rather mild brown, not too malty. Can't complain but can't get excited about another

beers.name: Yullis Gilbert Pinot Grigio wile ale
beers.desc: So beautifully sour in a tart way which doesn't linger in the mouth but sits on your lips. Drink it quick because it takes a while for the taste buds to adjust

beers.name: Wild beer madness IPA
beers.desc: Not as punchy as the label led me to believe put not too bitter and well balanced. More floral than citrus

beers.name: Feral B.F.H
beers.desc: Super floral in both smell and taste. Quite solid IPA despite the low ABV

beers.name: Blackfont aniversary ale
beers.desc: Slightly sour but that kinds of dominates everything else. It's decent but I think I might have left it too long in the fridge

beers.name: Knee deep stoutella
beers.desc: Way more nut than chocolate. Nicely creamy but still easy to drink

beers.name: Alesmith pale ale .394
beers.desc: Fruity and a solid pale ale. Easily sessionable

beers.name: Fullers 170th anniversary ale
beers.desc: Really missing the mark from what you expect with an aged ale

beers.name: Nomad freshie Moka
beers.desc: Surprisingly mild flavoured. Just a little hit of coffee and the gose sourness only comes through at the end a tiny bit. Nicely balanced and easy to drink

beers.name: Paddys IPA
beers.desc: Nice aroma but a little bitter and has some harshness in the back without any strong hop flavours coming through. Drinkable but not exciting

beers.name: Skorubrew #21 belgian pale ale
beers.desc: Has a really refreshing sweetness. Starts off really nice but gets a little off towards the end

beers.name: Trappistes rochefort 8
beers.desc: Really strong taste and aroma. Takes a little while to get used to but great towards the end

beers.name: White rabbit wolpertinger
beers.desc: Very interesting blend. The sourness mixed with the bitterness and floral flavours from the IPA somehow tastes sweet. A great beer if you want something different

beers.name: Tumut river Redneck ale
beers.desc: Has a little bit of sourness which could just be an old beer but overtakes a lot of the other flavours. Drinkable but not exciting

beers.name: Merchant smooth sailor
beers.desc: A little metallic but decent after that. A little creamy with a hint of chocolate

beers.name: SKOL
beers.desc: A little malty but not too much. Fairly easy drinking but there's nothing else to say

beers.name: Basement brewhouse helles lager
beers.desc: A little too bitter for my liking but easy drinking once you get used to it

beers.name: Capital evil eye
beers.desc: Nice hoppy aroma. Probably a little strong on bitterness but has a good red flavour. Really grows on you

beers.name: Sample lager
beers.desc: Fairly plain.  Has a little malty sweetness

beers.name: Goose midway session IPA
beers.desc: Starts out flavourful but it doesn’t last. Very inoffensive

beers.name: Blackmans Loral IPA
beers.desc: Strangely mild IPA. Sits well in the mouth

beers.name: Iron jack
beers.desc: Tastes like a watered down tooheys extra dry

beers.name: Skorubrew #24

beers.desc: Theres bitterness in the smell but it doesn’t carry through to the taste. What it does have is a whole bunch of fruity, hoppy flavours. Truely a session IPA, I could drink these all day

beers.name: 3 ravens xmas trifle shake
beers.desc: Doesn’t have that perfect haze but that doesn’t spoil the taste. Mild bitterness for an iPA without too many really strong hop flavours. Has a nice hint of custard both in smell and taste. Not something for everyday, but a nice little treat, just like trifle

beers.name: Clare valley red ale
beers.desc: A classic red ale. For some reason I was hoping for a brighter red but what can you do. Bitter to start with a sweet finish. One of those beers where the more you have the more you want it

beers.name: Feral dank blanc
beers.desc: Just a clean beer with a hint of fruit

beers.name: Balter IIPA
beers.desc: Had a super strong but clean ipa ness going on. Once again balter seeks to define what the standard should be

beers.name: Ballistic oaked XPA
beers.desc: The oak gives it a sweet smell, not sure how that works. Nice roundness and sits well as an XPA. Easy drinking with no harshness

beers.name: Cavalier brown
beers.desc: A little bit bitter for a brown and mostly mild otherwise. It’s not a bad beer, just not what I look for

beers.name: Zig zag Oakey Park ale
beers.desc: Very slightly Smokey smell and a fantastic roundness of flavour. No big flavours, just a well crafted beer

beers.name: Capital coast ale
beers.desc: Slightly tangy smell and tastes almost like a pilsner. But one with a subtle body and no aftertaste. Good for a hot day

beers.name: Big shed Astra XPA
beers.desc: Fairly easy drinking XPA with a tad of sweetness in the aftertaste. Beautiful golden clarity

beers.name: Stone and wood cloud catcher
beers.desc: Like the pacific ale but a little ale’y and more floral. Doesn’t evoke the same feelings of carefree bevving

beers.name: Prancing Pony Black Ale
beers.desc: Right from the first mouthful it hits you as a rich unashamedly. It’s actually not too heavy on the coffee side, more with toffee and caramel and slightly burnt flavours. It’s a smooth drink but I’m not sure if I could have many it

beers.name: Temple Dawn
beers.desc: Classic sour that’s exactly what you expect. No other big flavours, just a very sour beer. If you like sour beers then give it a try, otherwise you’ll probably be disappointed

beers.name: Barossa valley campfire session
beers.desc: Tastes like a strong English ale but it’s actually pretty low in aldohol. Slight caramel malt taste. Very easy drinking and smooth

beers.name: Western ridge friendly bison
beers.desc: Very unique style of hops and more bitter than I expected. Mostly dry with a very minor sweet after taste. Takes a while to get used to but good at the end

beers.name: Western ridge summerye
beers.desc: Seems more like a pilsner or a lager than a golden ale. Middle of the road but lacks anything to make me love it

beers.name: Sydney Pyrmont rye IPA
beers.desc: Best served a little warmer to let the roundness of the rye out a little. Interesting to see a more malt driven IPA, though it complements the fairly high bitterness well

beers.name: Western ridge topaz pride summer
beers.desc: Smells fresh but tastes like it’s from the west coast. It’s one to drink slowly

beers.name: Holgate gate keeper
beers.desc: Smells like a nice IPA, then you take a sip and it starts fine and ends up like water. Leaves me questioning why I’m even bothering to have a beer at all. I guess if you want something with just a tinge of hops and not much alcohol then this would be the beer for you

beers.name: Mornington new world lager
beers.desc: Nice tropical hoppy smell uncharacteristic of a lager. Tastes like a clean crisp lager without much bitterness. Just a little bit of biscuity citrusy goodness to balance it out. Perfect for a hot day

beers.name: Hargreaves hill ESB
beers.desc: I’m not usually a fan of ESB but this one’s pretty good. Reminds me of London ales but much smoother and not like someone put a cigarette in your beer. A little nutty with enough malt to smooth it out

beers.name: Young Henry’s afends hemp IPA
beers.desc: Has a very strange tinge to it. Can’t pick what it is, like something that wants to break through but there’s another flavour blocking it. Not for me

beers.name: Feral watermelon Warhead
beers.desc: I don’t usually like watermelon in beer but this works well with the sourness. I mean, it’s weak enough to be classed as water, but it’s a nice flavoured water

beers.name: Nomad red nosed reindeer
beers.desc: So I’m already drunk before opening this can so it’s probably clouding my review of what is a fairly heavy beer. It’s kind of low on the hops but heavy on the malt. Just couldn’t get into this

beers.name: Stockade MR Fruju NEIPA
beers.desc: The head on this looks like dish soap, probably because the beer is flat. Tastes a bit like dirty dishes as well. Gets a bit better as it goes down but never quite good

beers.name: Green beacon grappler lager
beers.desc: Fairly plain lager. I’ve had so many winners from this brewery that I thought they would make a lager actually amazing. Has a little bit of a sweet tinge but not much else to make it memorable

beers.name: Boatrocker beer garden pilsner
beers.desc: One of the better pilsners I’ve had. It’s distinctively a pilsner but mellow enough to not let that get in the way of being a nice summer beer

beers.name: СТАРОЃРАДСКО
beers.desc: Standard European pilsner. Smells dry and tastes malty

beers.name: Blackmans angry reg
beers.desc: Loving this super hoppy punch in the face. Lots of piney, dank hops but no lingering after taste. Going down faster than it should given the strength. Purchase only if you like strong IPAs

beers.name: Maat’s session lager
beers.desc: It’s an easy drinking lager with a little pilsner malt going on. Would be ok if it wasn’t a mid strength

beers.name: Krombacher pils
beers.desc: A nice mild pilsner, very German in its simplicity. A good hot weather beer

beers.name: Krombacher weizen
beers.desc: Beautiful orange colouring. Surprisingly creamy with lots of zesty flavours and a clean finish

beers.name: Stomping grounds wassail ale
beers.desc: A bit of a hearty winter ale, which might not fit the best with an Australian Christmas. Very smooth with malt coming through like toasted bread. I wish I had a few more

beers.name: Krombacher dark
beers.desc: Absolutely black beer but only really a little tinge in the taste

beers.name: Bridge road Hop rain
beers.desc: Very dank hops. Can definitely taste the difference with the wet hop

beers.name: Saucy Saison
beers.desc: Sometimes I forget how good a saison can be. That lovely mix of Belgian goodness and summery freshness

beers.name: New England Frederick India brown ale hop cannon
beers.desc: The name suggests they just threw every hip thing into a single beer. It’s surprisingly not an absolute mess. A sweet brown ale with a little hop kick just to top it off. Tasty and very drinkable

beers.name: Bucket boys don’t get caught with stout on your face
beers.desc: Super mellow stout

beers.name: Brick lane hoppy red
beers.desc: Very nice hop balance. Easy drinking and very enjoyable

beers.name: T-Bone pale ale
beers.desc: Great middle of the road pale ale. Enough hops to give it some flavour without becoming overwhelming and difficult to drink

beers.name: Iron house day tripper
beers.desc: It’s an ok mid strength

beers.name: Last rites Horn of diligence
beers.desc: Fairly plain pale ale

beers.name: White rabbit Teddywiddler
beers.desc: A nice tart ale. One of the better sours I’ve had recently

beers.name: Philter red session ale
beers.desc: Looks like sludge. Tastes ok, fairly smooth. Bit funny towards the end. Still not convinced this keg was ok

beers.name: Burleigh twisted palm
beers.desc: Makes me feel like it’s summer just drinking it. It’s not big on hop flavours but it’s enough to deliver the tropical notes that it promises. Maintains a refreshing taste

beers.name: Moo brew IPA
beers.desc: Bitter west coast IPA but well done. A good beer to get started with IPA

beers.name: Cloudy bay IPA
beers.desc: IPA with a little tang at the end

beers.name: Bruny island whey stout
beers.desc: Solid stout, has a nice creaminess from the whey. If you’re after a straight stout then it’s hard to fault this one

beers.name: Cascade pale ale
beers.desc: I’m at the brewery on a beautiful day after a long walk but this beer is brining me down a little. It’s just not a pale ale, it’s a lager

beers.name: Cascade draught
beers.desc: Standard lager

beers.name: Shambles Barry white
beers.desc: Nice creamy stout. Makes me happy

beers.name: Shambles dances with hops
beers.desc: Really floral IPA. Not too heavy on the bitterness

beers.name: T-bone fruit bowl IPA
beers.desc: Delivers well on the promise of fruit

beers.name: T-bone XPA
beers.desc: Well done XPA. Amazed they only do this seasonally given the popularity of the style

beers.name: Bruny Island oxymoron
beers.desc: Not really getting much of the pale hoppiness, it’s really just a dark beer. As such it’s ok, but nothing exciting

beers.name: Saucy pils
beers.desc: Very easy drinking and well rounded pils. Pretty happy with this

beers.name: Nomad South Pacific dream
beers.desc: Very fruity pale ale

beers.name: Basement brewhouse cereal offender
beers.desc: A little bit of a tangy IPA. Not that excited

beers.name: North end super alpha
beers.desc: Delivers on the zest it promises but the zest seems to give it a bit of a harshness in the back of the throat

beers.name: Prancing pony Zeppelin
beers.desc: A little harsh to start but rounds out. Doesn’t deliver the flavours it promises

beers.name: Brewmanity social beast
beers.desc: Fairly dry for a pale ale. No real hops coming through

beers.name: Bruny island farm ale
beers.desc: Really smooth and full bodied ale. No big flavours but very easy drink. Nice start to my foray into Tasmanian beers

beers.name: Iron house milk stout
beers.desc: Lacks the creamy finish that I love in a milk stout. Has the rest of what you would expect

beers.name: Warpigs rain of terror black IPA
beers.desc: Mellow without being too hoppy. There’s no big flavours on either side. It’s well balance but not enough to bring me back

beers.name: Feral biggie juice
beers.desc: Solid juicy IPA. Hard to decide whether to savour the taste or smash it down

beers.name: Uncle Kenny’s wakachangi
beers.desc: Has a distinctive but mild maltyness but otherwise easy drinking. Lives up to being quite nice beer

beers.name: Belhaven black
beers.desc: Very smooth and refreshing. No strong flavours makes it go down easy

beers.name: Old wives ale horn swatter
beers.desc: Kind of yeasty. Has rich smells but doesn’t carry through much into the taste

beers.name: 8 wired hippy Berliner
beers.desc: Interesting mix of hops and sour. But it’s fairly sweet which brings out the smell of the hops

beers.name: Eden phoenix
beers.desc: Nothing really amazing. Expected more

beers.name: Old wives ales lactohop
beers.desc: A bit sour, a bit of lacto but not much hops. Something different about this and really nice

beers.name: Rover Henty st ale
beers.desc: Slightly yeasty ale. Unexciting

beers.name: Brewhouse simcoe black ipa
beers.desc: Very nice mix of hops and malt

beers.name: Ballast point fathom IPA
beers.desc: Nice fresh IPA

beers.name: Toøl tropical rumble
beers.desc: Slightly tangy and very refreshing. Lots of fruit coming through. I can see why this brewery is highly rated

beers.name: Barossa valley Indian summer session ale
beers.desc: A little bit bland, but has some citrus notes and easy drinking on a hot day

beers.name: Bad Shepard Victoria pale ale
beers.desc: Fairly mild pale ale. Not much on the nose. More of a lager really. In that respect it’s good, but not enough to justify buying a craft beer

beers.name: 4 pines in season IPA
beers.desc: Interesting hop profile but not something that would keep me coming back

beers.name: Pact co Tennents peak double ipa
beers.desc: Solid DIPA with a nice roundness of flavour. Very smooth for what it is

beers.name: Yullis Hans gropo
beers.desc: Classic saison with not too much to turn someone off

beers.name: Batch chapeau
beers.desc: Tastes a lot like raspberry cordial. Too much sugar for me. I guess if you don’t like beer but want to get pissed then it would work for you

beers.name: Steerman blonde
beers.desc: Slightly tangy blonde. Hard to drink when it gets warm. Maybe I’m just being mean after drinking pure blonde

beers.name: Billy’s lager
beers.desc: Very plain Australian style lager. No real flavours at all which makes it easy to drink. It was cheap, but not worth going back for another

beers.name: Barossa Valley vitamin (B)eer
beers.desc: It’s a beer filled with super foods and therefore healthy. Red ale flavours mixed with the tartness of berries reminds me a little bit of berocca. Feels both fulfilling and refreshing

beers.name: Venom refreshing ale
beers.desc: Slightly tart and very refreshing. A little bit hoppy but not much. It’s cheap so I’m giving it a pass on being piss weak

beers.name: BiP
beers.desc: So I opened this bottle expecting another very plain European pilsner. But instead it has really biscuity taste and a huge amount of caramel in the smell. Despite that it’s still fairly light. Quite a unique mass market beer

beers.name: Newstead golden lager
beers.desc: Very hoppy for a lager but restrained enough to keep it refreshing

beers.name: 3 Ravens blended barleywine
beers.desc: Very strange to start, doesn’t smell like beer and it’s throwing me off. Taste is rich, sweet, malty and very smooth. A little bit like a mild and sweet whiskey. Still by the end I feel confused as to what I’m drinking. Interesting, but I wouldn’t try it again

beers.name: Coastal One mile pale ale
beers.desc: I’ve not seen the term Australian style pale ale before, as far as I can see this is just a lager. In that regard it’s better than mass market Australian lagers, but not enough to make it worth a purchase

beers.name: Claire valley double NEIPA
beers.desc: Most double IPAs are a punch in the face, this is mild and more malt driven. Rich and deep with no lasting flavours. Maybe the most dangerous beer I’ve had. Without knowing what it was you could just keep knocking these down

beers.name: Wayward dead dingo
beers.desc: Finished bottling #35 so time for a reward beer. It’s a crisp refreshing drop with just enough citrus hops to make it interesting. Gets better as it goes down

beers.name: Sherpa Himalayan red
beers.desc: A bit of rich redness with a pronounced bitterness. Smells like a lager but tastes richer

beers.name: Sierra Nevada session IPA
beers.desc: It’s mild and refreshing with a hint of hops at the end. Hops are more on the nose than in the mouth

beers.name: Harviestoun old engine oil
beers.desc: It’s a very rich beverage, but there’s a little toughness that spoils the smoothness

beers.name: Sierra Nevada resilience
beers.desc: Kind of boring. Very west coast IPA

beers.name: The garden milkshake IPA
beers.desc: Very full bodied IPA. Doesn’t give the fruit flavours it promises. Not something to smash down but great to savour slowly

beers.name: Green beacon uppercut
beers.desc: Strong bitter double IPA

beers.name: Murray coco hops
beers.desc: Fairly mild stout. Was hoping for a bit more body to hold the chocolate and coconut

beers.name: Big shed boozy fruit
beers.desc: So so so much fruit in this fella. If you can handle the bitterness it’s like a glass of beer juice. Delivers exactly what it promises

beers.name: Slipstream g-force
beers.desc: Nice fruity IPA, not that special but solid. Easy to drink and given the strength would knock you about easily

beers.name: Brouhaha New England IPA
beers.desc: Nice haze, fruity smell and a fresh taste. Basically just a smooth, easy drinking IPA

beers.name: One drop XPA
beers.desc: Great fruity drop. Not too much bitterness so good with food

beers.name: Slipstream Sabro strong pale ale
beers.desc: Really strange flavour that I can’t quite place. It tastes strong but there’s not actually that much alcohol. Takes a bit of getting used to. As I finally finish the last warm dregs I work out what the taste is, it’s a tiny hint of super tennents. Despite that, it’s not too bad

beers.name: Batch sky rocket in flight
beers.desc: Takes about 5 minutes just to settle.  It’s a slightly sour red but very mild in most ways. By the end I want more, but I don’t want to wait for it to settle again

beers.name: Basement brewhouse pilot #8 Brel
beers.desc: Kind of like spoiled wheat. Really strong smell which just doesn’t seem right. Can’t tell if this is off or just bad. Regardless, not a good beer

beers.name: Hope mango sour
beers.desc: A sour which doesn’t mess it up with too much sugar. The mango comes through but it’s properly transformed into a beer version. Refreshing

beers.name: Peach sauce
beers.desc: Peach not really coming through, it’s just a bit of a bland sour. Nothing to keep me coming back

beers.name: Spotty dog Portland pale ale
beers.desc: Plain pale ale. A little too bitter for my liking without much else. Tasted better while drinking around friends

beers.name: Panhead the vandal
beers.desc: Lots of floral notes. Doesn’t taste as strong as it is. Leaves a nice warmth in the stomach. Would actually be easy to get through a pint. Dangerously good

beers.name: One drop Botany Bay lager
beers.desc: Slightly rounded lager. Easy drinking not much else to say

beers.name: Basement brewhouse red right hand
beers.desc: It’s an ok red but only good enough for my left hand

beers.name: Mountain goat hello humanoid
beers.desc: Decent IPA with good dank bite. Seems a little thin and missing some roundness

beers.name: Basement brewhouse nikolaj
beers.desc: Almost creamy on the tip of the tongue with deliciousness all the way through

beers.name: Sierra Nevada Hazy little thing IPA
beers.desc: Bit more of a particulate haze than a real one, but maybe that’s my fault for forgetting it in the bottom of a box. A little bit tangy with a light mix of hops

beers.name: Dainton Matchstyx
beers.desc: Smells like vanilla and chocolate and so rich. But then you come to the taste and it just blows you away. You get both the chilli and the smoke are there but perfectly subtle so that they add to the beer without overwhelming it.  Leaves a lovely sense of warming inside and a beautiful sweetness on the palette/10

beers.name: Barossa Valley NAIPA
beers.desc: It’s got the hops and the kick of a NEIPA with a nice little bit of sweetness and a citrus tang. Smells good, looks good, tastes good

beers.name: Balter handsome elvis
beers.desc: Brew day finished, time for a beer. Really creamy stout due to the nitro but tastes a little bit overly bitter and doesn’t have much else flavour wise. That said it’s a good straightforward stout

beers.name: Hop nation karma
beers.desc: Super dark and very stouty. Nothing special but a very solid flavour

beers.name: Hop nation buzz
beers.desc: Comes off a little sweet and a little spicy

beers.name: Kaiju tapestry of chaos
beers.desc: Very mild sour. Good refreshing beer for a hot day. Too bad it’s winter. Very smooth and well crafted

beers.name: Ekim after battle
beers.desc: Kind of plain. Very inoffensive and easy to drink but nothing exciting

beers.name: Deschutes fresh haze
beers.desc: Fairly standard IPA, but gotta love that can

beers.name: Brouhaha milk stout
beers.desc: Pretty solid milk stout. Easy drinking  and well rounded

beers.name: Batch señor spicy
beers.desc: I don’t mind a bit of chilli in a beer but this is taking it over the top. My lips are stinging. Somehow leaves the flavour of corn chips in my mouth. An interesting experience, but not one I would repeat

beers.name: Deep creek misty miyagi
beers.desc: Lots of floral smells with a lot of hop freshness. Somehow this gets a bit lost in the taste, the bitterness comes through strong and overwhelms the rest

beers.name: 4 pines hefeweizen
beers.desc: Lots of banana. Very easy to drink. Great hefeweizen, middle of the road. Upset I haven’t had this sooner

beers.name: 4 pines queen bee IV
beers.desc: It’s a decent imperial. Fairly dead on for the style without any extras. Alcohol comes through a little strong but then it is a strong beer

beers.name: Coastal little street coffee milk stout
beers.desc: Good amount of coffee to beer ratio. Not enough caffeine to wake me up. Pretty good drinking

beers.name: Moon dog thunder lips
beers.desc: Tart citrus smell with a bitter taste that doesn’t have any strong hop flavours. Like a west coast IPA mixed with a little bit of a sour red

beers.name: Hemingways endeavour
beers.desc: With all the focus on east coast IPAs lately I forget how good a west coast IPA can be. Not too much dank pine in the hops nor too bitter with a strong floral aroma. Surprisingly easy to drink

beers.name: Rocks 2015 Russian imperial stout
beers.desc: Smells like boozy maple syrup. I shouldn’t be eating at the same. Outside of that it’s a good imperial and I want more

beers.name: Thunder road Big’N juicy
beers.desc: Fairly mellow IPA but enough to keep it interesting

beers.name: Hope Jet black IIIPA
beers.desc: Smells really mild and not much in the way of hops in the taste. The most prominent taste is really the alcohol. It’s not as bad as that might sound, it does fit together well and leaves me feeling happy and warm inside

beers.name: Ekim berserker amber IPA
beers.desc: Really good balance between amber and IPA flavours. Lots of malt and bitterness and a crisp smell

beers.name: Hemingway’s Doug’s courage
beers.desc: Seems a little too bitter for an XPA

beers.name: Moon dog old mate
beers.desc: Kind of yeasty, tastes cheap and not well put together at all. But it’s still beer

beers.name: Badlands dark side of orange
beers.desc: Like a mild orange chocolate mixed with beer. Could probably do with a bit more sweetness but good all round

beers.name: Wayward coffee and donuts
beers.desc: Leaves the taste of sugar donuts on the tip of your tongue. Like dunking donuts in coffee, but not good coffee. Interesting but I only want one

beers.name: Frenchies rosé brut IPA
beers.desc: Lots of sweetness coming through both in smell and taste. Doesn’t really seem like a beer, but who cares. Like beer mixed with champagne and raspberries
