beers.name: Shenanigans purple haze
beers.desc: Creaminess from the lactose comes through strong and there’s something else in there that I can’t pick. Not too full on despite the strength. Feeling very happy

beers.name: Hope tropical NEIPA
beers.desc: The amount of aroma coming off this is amazing, like smelling a fresh pineapple🍍. Taste is completely smooth and the bitterness is barely detectable. Even with food all the taste comes through

beers.name: McLeod’s last light
beers.desc: So strange to see this much flavour in what is essentially a light beer. Like weak coffee with a hint of oats

beers.name: Brooklyn summer ale
beers.desc: Quite clean and crisp with just a little malt that keeps it interesting

beers.name: Struman’s lager
beers.desc: Kind of a pilsner taste

beers.name: Bad shepherd vic ash pilsner
beers.desc: Tastes a bit like a pilsner with a hint of cigarettes. Not as awful as that my sound, but not a beer I would look for

beers.name: Mornington larrikin
beers.desc: Kind of a strange mix. Gets better as it warms otherwise the bitterness is a bit harsh

beers.name: Wolf of the willow Jalisco sour
beers.desc: Reminds me of a chilli beer but there’s no heat. Interesting but I don’t want another

beers.name: Garage project DFA
beers.desc: Just amazing from the first sip. Full of hops and quite bitter

beers.name: Garage project heels to Jesus
beers.desc: This beer would not stop foaming. Like a really light Belgian ale. Very enjoyable

beers.name: Mokke Bruin
beers.desc: Really mellow. Love these well made Belgian beers. Almost no hops, all malt focused

beers.name: Batch Tasman tango
beers.desc: Almost lagerish, or maybe my last beer was just too strong. Easy drinking but ultimately uninteresting

beers.name: Young Henry’s rumming with the devil
beers.desc: Only a little bit of raisin which is a good balance with the light brown ale flavours

beers.name: Young Henry’s double drop
beers.desc: Surprisingly light for a double IPA but doesn’t have anything to win you over

beers.name: Pirate life north west pale
beers.desc: Seems more like a malty IPA than a pale ale

beers.name: Holtland
beers.desc: Easy drinking lager

beers.name: Fixation squish
beers.desc: Nice amount of citrus and not too much bitterness leads to a well rounded pale

beers.name: Sierra Nevada stout
beers.desc: Creamy body and a rich stout flavour

beers.name: Moondog how now brown cacao
beers.desc: Very strange, expected a brown but it’s more of a slightly sour pale. Not so much bad, just not to style

beers.name: Lervig hazy days
beers.desc: Great amount of flavour for a lighter beer. Perfect introduction to a hazy ipa

beers.name: Sauce o ho! Cascadia
beers.desc: A dark hoppy beer. Well made but nothing special

beers.name: Balter hazy DC
beers.desc: Beautiful haze and a smell that you get from across the table. Mild and juicy

beers.name: New England bubbles in the orchard
beers.desc: Really wasn’t sure what to expect from this one, and still struggling as I finish it. The brut yeast mellows out the bitterness but also kills the hop flavours. Nothing in it really makes me want to find it again

beers.name: Sailors grave crystal healing
beers.desc: I really like the pickle mixed with the gose

beers.name: Moondog Edie’s IPA
beers.desc: Standard IPA with a little bit of dank hops

beers.name: Garage project muse
beers.desc: The lacto really comes through and works well with the lemon. Not at all like a beer, more like traditional lemonade

beers.name: Deep creek Aloha
beers.desc: Fairly standard sour meant for non beer drinkers

beers.name: La sirène season ale
beers.desc: Pours beautiful and clear. The smell is all Belgian farmhouse but the taste is more like a pale so it becomes a great blend of both. A good one to either savour or skull

beers.name: Little bang Galacotopus
beers.desc: Alcohol and barley are the only tastes that come through. And I wouldn’t say that it balances out that well. It just doesn’t make me happy

beers.name: Buxton brewery gatekeeper
beers.desc: Surprising to see so much packed into a beer with so little alcohol. Very well balanced porter, simple and drinkable

beers.name: Sauce the DIPA formally known as
beers.desc: Very mild for a double IPA, which isn’t to say its a mild beer, but just not as much punch as you might expect. Which just happened to be what I was after as I cooked dinner so I’m very happy with the flavour and a little bit tipsy

beers.name: Deschutes lil squeezy
beers.desc: A little bit more bitter than I think it should be which covers up some of the juicyness

beers.name: Bridge road nitro mountain lager
beers.desc: Very dark for a lager and strangely mild in flavour. Reminds me a little bit of an English hand pump bitter

beers.name: Akasha east NEIPA
beers.desc: Lots of orange coming through which is interesting but not balanced as it should be

beers.name: Yullis coffee nerd
beers.desc: The vanilla doesn’t come through very strong due to high bitterness and not much sweetness

beers.name: Wayward everyday ale
beers.desc: Quite a bit of bit for a pale ale but your get used to it quickly. Well named because it sits well as a standard beer

beers.name: Wayward IPA
beers.desc: Medium level west coast IPA. No big hop flavours coming past the bitterness but it’s what you expect from an IPA

beers.name: James squire hop theif 9
beers.desc: Strange that a hop thief beer would taste so malt driven. It comes off a lot like a cheap European lager

beers.name: Wayward pilsner
beers.desc: Not too malty like many pilsners. Like a lager with just a little bit extra flavour

beers.name: Mountain goat very enjoyable beer
beers.desc: Very lightly hopped pale ale. Great sessionable beer

beers.name: Coopers 2019 vintage
beers.desc: Too harsh for what it is

beers.name: Akasha captain famish
beers.desc: Light on bitterness with a pine and tropical finish. Gets a little rough as it warms but I guess I should just drink faster

beers.name: Big shed frankenbrown
beers.desc: Beautifully sweet and nutty brown ale. That balance where bitterness and sweetness work together perfectly

beers.name: Green beacon the whaler
beers.desc: Smells a lot of orange but only comes through a little in the taste. Kind of a mellow IPA with a little tang. Very easy drinking

beers.name: Coopers mild ale
beers.desc: Fairly dry and easy drinking ale. A little touch of fruity hops but not enough to make it interesting

beers.name: 4 pines mango pineapple NEIPA
beers.desc: Good amount of pineapple but not much mango. Strong bitterness but the citrus makes it easy drinking. It’s a nice NEIPA but there’s a lot better out there

beers.name: Two suns
beers.desc: Mix between a European malty lager and an Australian dry. It’s not too bad, pretty well crafted, but lacking any strong flavours

beers.name: Toøl mr blue
beers.desc: The fruit gives it a lot of tang but kind of masks the stout flavours even though the smell is there. Takes a lot of getting used to but even at the end I don’t think it works

beers.name: Garage project hippity dippity
beers.desc: Smells like being in a citrus orchard in bloom next to a Belgian brewery. I literally started drooling while smelling this. It’s like someone finally got a Belgian IPA right. Too much bitterness to have with food but a beer like this should be enjoyed by itself

beers.name: Stone enter night
beers.desc: Who makes a pilsner this strong? And why was Metallica involved? And it’s a decent pilsner, but with a slight harshness

beers.name: Hop nation dreamfeed
beers.desc: Decent hoppy IPA. Sufficiently juicy and not too heavy

beers.name: Garden brewery chocolate & peanut butter stout
beers.desc: Very rich and creamy with a lot of chocolate. Not getting much peanut butter but I think it’s just adding to the creaminess. Very low on bitterness. A great beer for a slow drink

beers.name: Two birds double sunset
beers.desc: One of the first double red ales I’ve had. The extra malt balances nicely against the additional alcohol and hops making it a good rounded beverage

beers.name: Willie the boatman rubi brown
beers.desc: Good sweet brown ale, has a little bit of smoke in there which doesn’t really fit. Overall doesn’t go down that smoothly

beers.name: Maui big swell
beers.desc: Heavy bitter west coast IPA

beers.name: Sauce lemon and lime bitterness units
beers.desc: Exactly as the name says, a lemon lime bitters as a beer. I do love bold flavour choices like this but balanced enough to be easy drinking

beers.name: Little creatures the fuggle is real
beers.desc: Solid middle of the road stout

beers.name: Three hills ALE
beers.desc: I mostly just bought this for the handle on the bottle. It’s a fairly normal malty beer, but has just has a little tang of something else

beers.name: Chur hashtag hops
beers.desc: Delivers a good bunch of dank hops. Easy drinking and full of booze and flavour

beers.name: Estrella Damm Inedit
beers.desc: This beer is already winning due to the amazing bottle. Apart from that it’s a fairly average wheat beer

beers.name: Yeastie boys hot space
beers.desc: Really interesting flavour that’s hard to place. Like an XPA with a dash of sweetness. A lot of flavour with very little alcohol

beers.name: Yullis Matt Steele
beers.desc: Very hoppy APA, wasn’t expecting it but exactly what I wanted

beers.name: Red hill wee heavy
beers.desc: Like beer with a little bit of extra alcohol. No hops and not much malt. Seems like a good winter beer

beers.name: Pirate life hoppy amber
beers.desc: Delivers exactly what it promises. The malt is a bit overridden by the bitterness of the hops but that’s to be expected. Solid middle of the road beer

beers.name: Little bang double west coast IPA
beers.desc: That’s some powerful punch in the face unadulterated west coast hops. Don’t see this much lately so it’s a refreshing change

beers.name: Little bang beard fiction
beers.desc: Great yet creepy can art. A lot nuttier than your usual APA which gives this beer a unique signature that is often lacking in craft beers looking to appeal to everybody. Would definitely choose this again

beers.name: Hawkers Circus OZ
beers.desc: Lightly hopped pale ale with a little extra booze. It’s what you expect from a strong pale but it’s not that exciting

beers.name: Chateu du tasman into the lime light
beers.desc: Not too strong on the sourness which I like. More of a refreshing light zesty beer

beers.name: Fathom belgian style brown
beers.desc: Strangely sweet and tangy for a brown. Takes a bit of getting used to and not particularly special

beers.name: Akasha cryo IPA
beers.desc: A mostly piney IPA. Has that perfect level of heavyness for an IPA. Not too bitter to have with food

beers.name: Thunder road dark and creamy
beers.desc: Doesn’t taste as fruity as it looks, just has a little tang and otherwise it’s a fairly plain IPA

beers.name: Moondog cake hole
beers.desc: Really rich and does remind me of cake. I feel like I’m not devoting enough attention to this and am missing some flavours. Still nice

beers.name: Foxhat heavy handed XPA
beers.desc: Very creamy XPA. Exactly what you expect and nothing else

beers.name: Modus operandi Pangea
beers.desc: It’s good but nothing to write home about

beers.name: Brewhouse echo flare
beers.desc: Very nice mix of hops that brings nothing to the front but melds together

beers.name: Garage project amber ale
beers.desc: Seems very unexciting. Like’s it’s almost great, but just ends up average

beers.name: Thunder road coconut porter
beers.desc: Fairly mild porter with a very nutty smell to it, but not really any coconut. Overall enjoyable and easy to drink

beers.name: Old wives ale old man yells at cloud
beers.desc: Beautiful colouring with a somewhat creamy texture. Seems to be a mix of piney and floral hops that comes out mild and juicy. Would go for another

beers.name: Basement #21 hazelnut and chocolate milk stout
beers.desc: I’m a big fan of hazelnut and chocolate in a beer. This one is pretty light on but it gives a great creamy finish

beers.name: Kona gold cliff ipa
beers.desc: Very tropical but not bitter enough to have problems with food

beers.name: Six strings blood orange vanilla magik
beers.desc: A lot packed into a kolsch. Hard to pick out the individual flavours but there’s a nice level of sweetness.  Some gulps give vanilla and others orange

beers.name: Beerfarm Royal haze
beers.desc: Super tropical IPA. Makes me feel like I’m on a beach with some chilled tunes and a plate of fruit

beers.name: New England shredded and zested
beers.desc: Very unique. Was expecting sourness but it’s more like eating a bitter pie. Nice to start but now I feel like I’ve eaten a whole pie. Don’t order a pint

beers.name: Fixation little ray
beers.desc: A little tangy, a little bitter and a little fruity. Good mix that makes it easy to drink

beers.name: Nine fingers brew
beers.desc: Smells a little piney but tastes really rounded and malty

beers.name: Quiet deeds juice train
beers.desc: Juicy, tangy and surprisingly light

beers.name: Batch aprikviek IPA
beers.desc: Very mild apricot in a slightly tangy beer. It’s an abnormal combination but it works

beers.name: Wayward hazy brau
beers.desc: Malty IPA which hits the roof of your mouth. A good dinner IPA

beers.name: James squire mad brewers
beers.desc: Raspberry is noticeable straight away. Ok to start, but by the end of a pint there’s just too much sweetness

beers.name: Forst
beers.desc: Slightly malty lager. Tastes better than it smells

beers.name: Hop nation the heart
beers.desc: Really nice pale. Nice pine finish

beers.name: Kangaroo island amber ale
beers.desc: Very mild, but with a little kick of malty flavour. Smooth and works well no matter what temperature

beers.name: Drunken drone honey wheat ale
beers.desc: A little yeasty and a tad of sweetness. Very fizzy carbonation. A good introduction to wheat beers

beers.name: Kangaroo island pale ale
beers.desc: Fairly lacklustre pale. Hasn’t gotten much in the way of aromatics from the hops

beers.name: Greenock bundawunda blonde
beers.desc: Yeasty to the point of almost being sour with a light fizz

beers.name: Greenock dark ale
beers.desc: Plain dark sessionable ale

beers.name: Ballistic pale ale
beers.desc: Surprisingly deep pale ale. Lots of smooth bitterness

beers.name: Prost
beers.desc: Slightly tangy or yeasty which removes some of the refreshingness on a hot day

beers.name: Stark IPA
beers.desc: Not a great amount of hops. Actually probably stronger on the malt which is strange. Now that I read the label it’s because it’s an Indonesian pale ale

beers.name: Stark 1945
beers.desc: Tastes like a European lager or perhaps a pilsner. Heavy on the malt but quite nice and clean

beers.name: Bali hai
beers.desc: Light malty lager. Tastes a bit like it's devoid of a soul

beers.name: San Miguel negra
beers.desc: Fairly standard porter. Thin but with rich toasty flavours

beers.name: Anker lychee
beers.desc: Very slight beer flavour coming through the lychee. Pretty much a waste of time considering the low ABV

beers.name: Stark mango ale
beers.desc: Slightly bitter mango juice. At least it looks like beer I guess

beers.name: Tumage red ale
beers.desc: So happy to find something like this in Bali. Classic red ale. Full rounded malt with only a little bitterness. Very easy to drink and still refreshing

beers.name: Tumage pale ale
beers.desc: Slightly yeasty but otherwise a clean refreshing pale ale. Fairly low on hops but fits in well with the hot humid weather

beers.name: Two birds hopped across the ditch
beers.desc: Very crisp pilsner with just a tinge of hops

beers.name: Bridge road beechy xpa
beers.desc: Slightly lighter than the balter XPA. Would make a good session ale

beers.name: Akasha hop till you drop
beers.desc: Smells floral and sweet. Almost like elderflower. Taste is more on the dank side

beers.name: Deeds best coast IPA
beers.desc: Smells very piney, not a lot on the taste side, bitterness kind of covers it up

beers.name: Firestone walker mind haze
beers.desc: Beautiful colour with a very mild slightly lemony smell. Very mild on hops and slightly sour. No big flavours but could have a few of these

beers.name: Bodriggy muckamuck stout
beers.desc: Purely black and very thick. Super toasty smell of coffee. Taste is smooth with mild bitterness and warming my stomach . It’s only a small beer but it’s going straight to my head. Great stout for quickly elevating your drunkenness

beers.name: Philter troppo
beers.desc: There’s a really strange smell and flavour. Maybe a very faint stale vomit flavour but it comes and goes. Could just me being sensitive to some chemical. Sadly there’s not much else to it to mask that

beers.name: Bodriggy utopia
beers.desc: Nice hops on the nose with just a tinge of bitterness.  Nothing to win me over but a solid drink

beers.name: Basement south coast pale ale
beers.desc: Strange peppery flavour, doesn’t really taste like a pale. Seems a bit wrong

beers.name: Pirate life easy ale
beers.desc: Little bit of flavour but still easy to use as a session beer

beers.name: Vibrant forest pupa
beers.desc: Has a great hazy colour. Smells like a mix between stone fruit and citrus hops. Flavour is a bit weaker than expected but very pleasant

beers.name: Pickled monkey Kong IPA
beers.desc: Creamy mouthfeel with a big punch of hops

beers.name: Wayward lumberjack
beers.desc: Very sweet for an IPA. Maybe Canadians like maple syrup in their IPA? Not too many   strong flavours but a solid IPA bitterness. Hard to describe why, but I really enjoy this

beers.name: Batch Buckley St brown
beers.desc: Very little smell and very clean on the palette. A little sweetness and not much else. Very easy drinking

beers.name: Hairyman cory’s claim
beers.desc: Very rich dark ale. Sweet and malty towards the end of the sip with a bit of nuttiness

beers.name: Young Henry’s NEIPA
beers.desc: Fruity but sour with just a bit too much yeast. Not sure if I need more or less

beers.name: Murray’s laguna
beers.desc: Surprisingly sweet for an IPA which makes it dangerously easy to drink

beers.name: Hope chocolate milk porter
beers.desc: Very chocolaty

beers.name: Zytho brewing IPA
beers.desc: It’s got a bit of a hop kick to start but not enough depth to carry it through. You get some tasty earthy flavours and then it’s just gone

beers.name: Pirate life açaí and passionfruit sour
beers.desc: Been keeping away from sours but couldn’t resist trying out something new from PL. Mild all round but work well as an easy drink

beers.name: Nomad budgy smuggler
beers.desc: Very floral to start but not too much behind it so it’s still easy to drink. Reminds me a bit of the pirate life pale ale

beers.name: James squire broken shackles
beers.desc: Smells like a slightly off European lager. Tastes about the same, like some fruity zest wants to come through but it’s caught up in mediocrity

beers.name: Hawkes Steph likes a party
beers.desc: Smells like a strong west coast IPA and at first tastes like one but doesn’t hit as hard as expected, probably because there’s a caramel sweetness to balance it out

beers.name: Hope mango hazy IPA
beers.desc: Smells like a glass of mango juice. A lot of mango in the taste but there’s still a lot of bitterness so it’s still beer. Easy drinking and full of flavour. A real treat

beers.name: Boatrocker stout
beers.desc: Classic malty stout

beers.name: Ocean beach brewing pain killer sour
beers.desc: It’s very sour, gives the dry lips a little tingle. Has that slightly off taste that I found in proper Belgian sours. Has a little bit of pineapple but it’s overpowered by the yeast

beers.name: Kaiju demon cleaner
beers.desc: Very strong bitterness, nothing special

beers.name: One drop re-up
beers.desc: Dank IPA but very mild. Easy drinking but interesting

beers.name: Tinnies XPA
beers.desc: Fresh tropical vibes me very smashable

beers.name: Tinnies pale ale
beers.desc: Very mild on flavour

beers.name: Cervisiam jungle juice
beers.desc: The strong dank IPA that I needed at the end of a long day of work. Mild enough to make it easy to drink

beers.name: Tizzle tazzle
beers.desc: Standard sour, fairly strong on blueberry. A good level of bitterness vs sweetness for my taste

beers.name: Akasha queen of the damned
beers.desc: Exactly on point

beers.name: Prancing pony India red ale
beers.desc: It’s a real alcohol kick in the face but not too much else coming through

beers.name: Cervisiam impeached
beers.desc: Strong sour with a heavy peach flavour

beers.name: Woolshed firehouse stout
beers.desc: There’s a lot of coffee in this one, actually too much for a non coffee drinker like me. Very smooth

beers.name: Mismatch pizza beer
beers.desc: Initially it just seems like any lager, but it does have a softer mouthfeel. There’s nothing exciting the smell

beers.name: Deeds Lavington
beers.desc: Beautiful dark red colour, Smells a little sweet but very light. Doesn’t taste much like lamington but it’s a nice soft stout

beers.name: Mountain culture status quo
beers.desc: So happy with this beer. Super fruity and light as well. But most of all I’m just happy to be somewhere that has great beer on tap

beers.name: Ocean reach grapefruit IPA
beers.desc: A little bit of grapefruit adds to the bitterness and gives a little sweetness. It’s good but doesn’t rise above other IPAs

beers.name: Sailors Grave Lemon Meringue Cream Sour
beers.desc: A lot milder than it sounds. Imagine a creamy pale ale with a dash of lemon. Nice bit of tang

beers.name: Zamkowe
beers.desc: Malt taken up to the next level but without coming off too cheap. Not sure how many you could have before it became overwhelming

beers.name: Nikšićko pivo
beers.desc: Standard Eastern European beer. Not much to say really

beers.name: Urbanaut summerland
beers.desc: Not salty enough. Comes out more like lemonade than beer. Great if that’s what you want, but I like beer

beers.name: Mismatch traditional stout
beers.desc: Very robust stout. Rich deep roasted flavours but light on the coffee. Surprisingly easy to drink which feels like I could have quite a lot of these

beers.name: One drop T3020
beers.desc: It’s decent but there’s no real selling point to bring me home. Drink it as an easy bev but that’s it

beers.name: Young Henry’s rye IPA
beers.desc: Love the rounded ness of a good rye IPA. Yes it’s a little harsh but it’s where it needs to be. Take that bitter hit and learn to love it

beers.name: Hop nation dreamfeed
beers.desc: Fairly mild for a strong IPA and a bit juicy.      Rounded and easy to drink. A good one to start on today

beers.name: Little bang may contain traces of panther
beers.desc: Very run of the mill dark beer. But that’s not really a complaint. There’s something to say for a well executed classic

beers.name: White bay uniformity of form
beers.desc: Has a really mild dank kick underneath more floral notes. Quite different but not in a shocking way

beers.name: Hope juicy mango hazy sour
beers.desc: Like drinking unripe mango. Slightly thicker than a normal beer which leaves a sweet mango residue on your lips. Brilliant refresh between some other strong IPAs

beers.name: Deeds double time
beers.desc: Something off about this one. It’s a little sour and bitter but without much to make me want it

beers.name: Moon dog tropical lager
beers.desc: Slightly fruity lager. Not a lot else to say

beers.name: Hope lemon lime sour
beers.desc: Tastes like a vodka lime soda. Kind of nostalgic from my younger days. Loses half a point because there’s not enough booze

beers.name: Moon dog lager
beers.desc: Malty European tasting garbage

beers.name: One drop quadzilla
beers.desc: Kind of a cross between the overhopped level of a west coast with the floral flavours of an east coast IPA.  Surprisingly easy to drink given the hop levels

beers.name: Gipsy hill metro
beers.desc: Very sweet for a hoppy beer. Very nice

beers.name: Pirate life Kakadu plum lemon myrtle
beers.desc: It’s one of the strangest beers I’ve had. The first sip was awful, but it slowly gets better. It’s just such unfamiliar flavours, but still very much beer. Gets extra points for being interesting

beers.name: Little bang inside voice
beers.desc: Nicely sweet stout with a little tang

beers.name: Little bang icon
beers.desc: Fairly standard pale ale

beers.name: Endeavour amber ale
beers.desc: Strong malty smell but not as strong in the taste. Good mild amber

beers.name: Grand ridge winter warmer
beers.desc: Just a hint of chilli which fits well with the rich sweetness of the stout. It actually does a good job of warming my insides. A little bit much

beers.name: Slow lane thirsty miner
beers.desc: Very heavy Belgian yeasty flavour in an otherwise light beer. Went well to cut through some spicy Thai

beers.name: Wild spirit yuzu sour
beers.desc: Fairly standard sour. Not much sweetness

beers.name: Ocean reach oatmeal stout
beers.desc: Perfect relaxation beer. You would not guess that it’s an 8% beer. But straight from the first sip it fills me with a gentle relaxation. It’s got slight bite from the roasted malt but it mellows out and goes down easy

beers.name: Bay rd smoked ESB
beers.desc: Beautiful looking amber beer. Has just that right level of smoke to make it interesting. Very interesting style of beer worth trying

beers.name: Panhead Sucky Monmon
beers.desc: Fairly standard lager. The can brought me in but there's not enough to keep me

beers.name: Jetty road infinite 8
beers.desc: Very light aroma and a surprisingly mellow taste. A very sophisticated IIPA not trying to hit any crazy levels

beers.name: Deschutes obsidian stout
beers.desc: There’s a very strange flavour in this stout, almost a sourness but not quite. Perhaps it’s a bunch of mild flavours mixed in together

beers.name: Slow lane foundation
beers.desc: Fairly relaxed farmhouse ale. Nice tinge of yeast but restrained. Very easy drinking and well made

beers.name: Bay rd cake chaser
beers.desc: Leaves a little sweetness on the lips and does seem slightly reminiscent of a heavy cake. Basically a sweet stout but very drinkable

beers.name: Six strings mr black
beers.desc: Not as much coffee as I was expecting. Actually a fairly mild easy drinking stout

beers.name: Beerfarm IPA
beers.desc: Fairly mild west coast style IPA with a bit of pine and floral

beers.name: Hope smoked porter
beers.desc: That’s a lot of smoke. I’m ok with the level, but I wouldn’t recommend it

beers.name: Hop & Clover pale ale
beers.desc: Somehow tastes sweet and bitter at the same time

beers.name: Batch ginu-pine
beers.desc: Very faint pineapple that gives the sour a little tang

beers.name: Batch lemon meringue pie
beers.desc: Really nice mix of dessert and beer. Just a tinge or sweetness

beers.name: Batch helles lager
beers.desc: Seems really bitter after some sours. Has the maltyness of a European lager but not as strong

beers.name: Batch campos milk stout
beers.desc: It’s basically like drinking a cold coffee. Very smooth and creamy

beers.name: Batch big tex’s ipa
beers.desc: Really rounded IPA. Lots of bitterness but without many strong hop flavours

beers.name: Sauce Idaho secret
beers.desc: My favourite thing today. Super mellow, and great for a slow drink

beers.name: Sauce oat and about
beers.desc: Rich and mellow

beers.name: Bay rd west coast IPA
beers.desc: Slightly piney IPA. Not too much of a punch in the face

beers.name: Holgate hazy IPA
beers.desc: Delivers the haze that it promises with a little bit of sweetness. Great smell and an easy drink

beers.name: Beerfarm milk stout
beers.desc: Heavy stout with lots of coffee and chocolate

beers.name: Burleigh smokin’
beers.desc: Very chocolatey on the first sip but that gives way to a mild smoke. Very interesting to see the clean palate character of a lager works with some smoke and dark malts

beers.name: Big shed californicator west coast IPA
beers.desc: Very clear and great from the first taste. It’s got west coast hops but it’s not in your face, very restrained

beers.name: Bay rd dark cherry wheat
beers.desc: It’s kind of strange, like a kriek mixed with a porter. Very thin so it’s fairly easy to drink but not exciting

beers.name: One drop DDH Oat cream IPA
beers.desc: Smells really juicy and it is quite a juicy IPA, almost to the point of having a tang. Probably not enough cream for the name

beers.name: Tall boy and moose Major moose
beers.desc: Very mild classic brown ale. A little bit of sweetness and then clean after that

beers.name: Dainton bounty hunter
beers.desc: All sorts of dessert flavours in this one. You wouldn’t want more than one, and probably at the end of the night

beers.name: Mountain culture eudaimonia
beers.desc: It’s thick and sweet but somehow you can’t even taste the booze. Tastes like a glass of sultanas. My whole body feels warm afterwards. I’m ok with it, but I wouldn’t got back

beers.name: Beerfarm strawberry gum stout
beers.desc: It’s got a lovely red colour tinge to it and a bit of extra fruity sweetness for an otherwise standard stout. But it’s good and grows on you the more you have

beers.name: Founders curmudgeon 2017
beers.desc: Super well rounded, and easy to drink. Heavy whisky notes with just the right amount of sweetness. Going to be hard to beat

beers.name: Akasha tropical fruit storm hazy ipa
beers.desc: Super fruity and juicy without being harsh or sour at all

beers.name: White bay where ever I rove
beers.desc: Solid IPA. Nothing big, but some good drink juice

beers.name: Amager bryghus la Santa muerte
beers.desc: Hit in the face with the barley wine of this. Somehow both I feel like I need more and have had enough

beers.name: St feuillien brune
beers.desc: Tastes kind of metallic to start. Once that goes away there’s a richness to it but still much lighter then from the look of it. Good by the end

beers.name: Wayward cashmere cat
beers.desc: Velvety smooth and delicious. Really light on hops for a hazy IPA but it’s great to have something you can

beers.name: Wayward otro
beers.desc: Kind of a gose mix with a pale ale. Mellow drinking and a good transition drink

beers.name: Wayward beware the Ides märzen
beers.desc: Hard to describe. Like a pilsner but way more rounded. Very low on bitterness

beers.name: Wayward the darkness stout
beers.desc: Smells all of coffee but it’s milder in the taste

beers.name: Wayward weisse rauchbier
beers.desc: Just a little bit smokey, mostly mild lager

beers.name: White bay sunny pale
beers.desc: It’s similar to stone and wood. But not as good

beers.name: Battler bitter
beers.desc: Like a bitter, pale and pilsner had a baby. Great beer for a hot day

beers.name: Badlands brewbacca
beers.desc: Love the name and love a kolsch. The top of the can says “Dangerously Drinkable”, but I would say the motto should just be drinkable. It’s not quite crisp enough and a bit too malty, more like a pilsner

beers.name: Nomad Trooper
beers.desc: Not my favourite XPA

beers.name: Hop nation bearded seal
beers.desc: Really smooth and full of hops

beers.name: Bright black diamond
beers.desc: A little bit of extra malt and some extra hops

beers.name: Temple cakepricot
beers.desc: Smells a bit like cake. Tastes sweet and and a little bit apricoty. It’s very strong and you wouldn’t want to have many

beers.name: Lord Howe island phasmid
beers.desc: Earthy pale ale

beers.name: Big shed double hazing
beers.desc: Mellow and rich

beers.name: Sailors grave Milky Way custard apple cream sour
beers.desc: Actually delivers on the random bunch of words on the can. Impressive execution

beers.name: One brew nation DDH hazy pale ale
beers.desc: Hops and lime. Kind of works, but really not necessary. By the end I was happy to be done with it

beers.name: Bondi beach IPA
beers.desc: Strong yet mellow west coast IPA

beers.name: Little bang sludge beast
beers.desc: There’s a lot of everything in this one. The stout and coffee is almost overpowering to start with, afterwards it becomes a nice slow drink. Despite the amount of flavour I could happily go another

beers.name: Akasha little smith IPA
beers.desc: It’s nice but there’s not enough in it to call it an IPA

beers.name: Akasha stone fruit IPA
beers.desc: Smells like beer and fruit and full of flavour. Overtime the grapefruit builds up

beers.name: Akasha double hazy
beers.desc: Smells all of mango but is milder in taste. Fairly standard juicy IPA

beers.name: Akasha east v west
beers.desc: Very rich IPA but perfectly balanced

beers.name: Garage project cereal milk stout
beers.desc: The nitro in this makes it oh so creamy and smooth. The perfect breakfast drop

beers.name: CoConspirators double butcher
beers.desc: Smells like a double IPA and tastes like a strong red ale. It’s a drink to savour and enjoy slowly else the bitterness becomes overwhelming

beers.name: Pirate life dddh cryo NEIPA
beers.desc: Fairly mild NEIPA, easy drinking and a good lead in to stronger beers

beers.name: Capital slam dunk TIPA
beers.desc: Really rich but surprisingly easy to drink

beers.name: Kerbside two juicy pale ale
beers.desc: Tasty light but fruity beverage

beers.name: Coconspiritors the postman
beers.desc: Really good, deep IPA that reminds me of older west coast IPAs but with more refinement and less in your face bitterness

beers.name: Bondi white coffee stout
beers.desc: Probably the #1 beer for not looking like it tastes. It smells like coffee beans and tastes like a black coffee with a hint of beer. This would be better for someone who knows what coffee should taste like

beers.name: Little alchemist black magic
beers.desc: It’s a lot lighter tasting than it looks. It’s not really strong

beers.name: Brick lane supernova IPA
beers.desc: Bitter west coast IPA low on aromatics

beers.name: Six strings oat cream IPA
beers.desc: Super creamy but almost with a little bit of tang due to citrus hops. Very strange but keeps you coming back

beers.name: Coopers hazy IPA
beers.desc: It’s an ok beer, but not a hazy IPA

beers.name: Otherside harvest red ale
beers.desc: Pretty light red ale

beers.name: Sailors grave embers red IPA
beers.desc: Very high on the bitterness but as that rounds out it shows off a great beer

beers.name: Mountain culture double red IPA
beers.desc: Very rich red ale with a good kick

beers.name: One drop hazy
beers.desc: Really nice smell. A little much of a tang after the oat IPA I had. Pretty good

beers.name: One drop rum barrel aged nitro stout
beers.desc: So much sweetness makes it seem like it’s so much stronger. Gets more agreeable towards the end

beers.name: One drop experimental pale ale
beers.desc: Not sure about what this is supposed to be. More of a hazy IPA but milder

beers.name: One drop strawberry milkshake
beers.desc: Smells and tastes like a strawberry cream lolly that I had as a kid

beers.name: One drop bitter and black
beers.desc: Basically it’s Thai basil in a glass. Not sure how they managed this but it’s intense. I really love strange and interesting flavours but don’t have this in large quantities

beers.name: Social bandit passive aggressive
beers.desc: That pour is a sediment filled mess and the beer itself tastes like there’s something burnt in there. As the sediment settled that got much better. It’s like a sour mixed with a pale ale

beers.name: Brick lane all together
beers.desc: Just a little bit of dank and a little sweetness that really pulls this beer together

beers.name: Riverside tropico
beers.desc: Fairly mild juicy IPA, almost towards a pale ale. Might be lacking on big tastes but good for a session

beers.name: Beerfarm asam boi gose
beers.desc: Plum is always really strange in a beer but this doesn’t go too far

beers.name: Two bays IPA
beers.desc: Strangely sweet. I didn’t think gluten free would work but the different grains really give a unique taste. Quite thin for the flavour

beers.name: Red right hand ddh red ipa
beers.desc: More like a strong red ale than an IPA with some extra bitterness. Not complaining because it works well and is easy to drink for the strength

beers.name: Riverside hex
beers.desc: A little bit Heavy on the bitterness

beers.name: Riverside brave new world
beers.desc: Slightly bitter but not exciting

beers.name: Atomic pale ale
beers.desc: Just what I needed to start the evening, but it was kind of bland by the end

beers.name: Atomic IPA
beers.desc: Has a strange flavour initially but overall it’s just a kind of mid ground IPA

beers.name: Atomic XPA
beers.desc: Solid fruity XPA

beers.name: Atomic Cryo red alert
beers.desc: Very good red, rich and deep with a nice malty and bitter aroma. Exactly as a red should be

beers.name: Atomic cashmere
beers.desc: Absolutely delivers on the pear and in being a proper saison. Rare to see but easy to drink

beers.name: Atomic first cab strong ale
beers.desc: It’s very bitter, but maybe it’s missing something

beers.name: Atomic Paul’s porter
beers.desc: Lots of coffee on the nose and nice roasted flavours in the taste

beers.name: Akasha double queen
beers.desc: Really deep red without much bitterness. it hits the tip of the tongue full of malt but then just melts away and leaves me wanting more

beers.name: Akasha the eagle
beers.desc: Reminds me a lot of the feral tusk. Strong enough to warm on the way down. Not really much flavour though

beers.name: Zytho tropical haze
beers.desc: Tastes a lot of mandarin which fits with the tropical name. A bit thin but it’s ok

beers.name: Frenchies Fresh Harvest IPA
beers.desc: Very bitter to start but then after it rounds out there’s not much left. Maybe I shouldn’t have ordered craft beer from a burger shop

beers.name: Nomad rollin haze
beers.desc: Nice citrus smell and a little bit of haze on top of a mild pale ale. Easy drinking with a little tang

beers.name: Quakers red rye IPA
beers.desc: Very mild on the rye with just a tinge to add more to the IPA and take out some of the bitterness

beers.name: Devils hollow nosey bob
beers.desc: Pretty much all malt with only a tinge of hops

beers.name: Sneaky bucha XPA
beers.desc: Basically a beer with some kombucha poured in. Smells tangy but still tastes of beer. It’s good, but not how I want beer

beers.name: Sparkle to bee or not to bee
beers.desc: It’s a very mild stout.  Not a lot to it, but easy drinking and palatable

beers.name: Local pacific paradise
beers.desc: Very middle of the road, but that’s ok

beers.name: James squire honey bee
beers.desc: The honey gives it a little tang and sweetness, but really it’s not much off a standard lager

beers.name: James squire stormy seas
beers.desc: Very mild stout, a little bit of sweetness. Enough to keep it interesting

beers.name: James squire 4 bushels
beers.desc: Good amount of yeasty bananas coming through. Surprisingly on point

beers.name: Feral west coast IIPA
beers.desc: Super rich IPA. A little floral but mostly piney and earthy

beers.name: Stone and wood The gatherer
beers.desc: Don’t like the watermelon but the cucumber rounds it out. It doesn’t keep me coming back, but it’s a great quencher

beers.name: Bridge road fresh haze
beers.desc: Very interesting set of flavours but it’s too faint and disjointed to make this a winner

beers.name: Bracket east coast hazy IPA
beers.desc: It’s somehow mild and full at the same time. It’s a good strong staple beer

beers.name: Bracket passionfruit sour
beers.desc: Like a beer version of passioa. Perfect level of sour and no sweetness to make it poppy. Maybe not my favourite beer, but one of my favourite sours

beers.name: Bracket Vienna lager
beers.desc: Malty on the tongue but then dry afterwards. Perfectly fits the style

beers.name: Bracket west coast IPA
beers.desc: Perfectly rich west coast IPA

beers.name: Hop nation mirror mirror
beers.desc: Very tangy and too focused on the juice while ignoring the beer. Just too many random letters for a boring beer

beers.name: Hawkes opener IPA
beers.desc: Probably more of a pale than an IPA, but the flavour combination is good

beers.name: Wayward bru haze
beers.desc: Solid hazy IPA

beers.name: Newy pacific lager
beers.desc: The best lager I’ve had in a long time. Flavours of an XPA but very light

beers.name: Stone neverending haze IPA
beers.desc: Has a sweet tang which is pretty nice. But it’s not an IPA, as it warms the bitterness comes through and takes away from the sweetness. Ok, but lying about what it is

beers.name: Coopers dry
beers.desc: Surprisingly malty for what is called a dry beer. But it’s easy drinking with a good flavour and refreshing

beers.name: Local beer XPA
beers.desc: A very slight orange taste, which is well balanced but also underwhelming. Not bad, just meh

beers.name: Initial XPA
beers.desc: Has a little tropical flavour, but only in the taste and not smell

beers.name: Byron bay hazy lager
beers.desc: Really on point, clean lager with a little extra flavour

beers.name: Pirate life south coast pale ale
beers.desc: Good mix of hops and freshness

beers.name: Scharers lager
beers.desc: A little malty at the start but a rather fresh lager after that

beers.name: 4 pines freshy extra refreshing
beers.desc: Pretty disappointed, just a boring beer

beers.name: Endeavour hoppy days
beers.desc: Nice hoppy beer with a little bit extra in there

beers.name: Balter Lager
beers.desc: A very sweet lager, though this one is past it’s best. Still pretty good

beers.name: Pirate life Idaho-7
beers.desc: Smells refreshing but much heavier in the taste. Not bad

beers.name: Bracket cashmere pilsner
beers.desc: Slightly mild pilsner with just a little kick of hops

beers.name: Bracket helles bock
beers.desc: Leaves a strange film on the top of the mouth, but there’s a sweetness that lingers and brings you back in. The kind of beer you finish before you know it

beers.name: Bracket dry hopped wild ale
beers.desc: Super middle ground between a sour and a pale ale. The flavour isn’t perfected but it’s a nice mix

beers.name: Mountain culture Yipee Ki Yay
beers.desc: Beautiful thick haze but not nearly as punchy as you would think to look at it. Lots of tropical notes wafting off but it’s a rather mild IPA with hints of pineapple which focuses on getting the flavours right. It would be easy to knock back a lot of these, perhaps I’m just excited to kick off the advent calendar

beers.name: Seven  mile the extra mile
beers.desc: Lovely colouring and a very rich west coast IPA, just enough booze to give that warm feeling. No big flavours I can pick, but very rounded

beers.name: Batch choc orange porter
beers.desc: Just a tinge of orange and pretty mild all round. My burps taste a little like jaffas

beers.name: Dark sour of the moon
beers.desc: Nice level of sour which mixes well. Hard to really pick that it’s a beer though

beers.name: Basement Who is your daddy and what does he brew
beers.desc: A little creamy in texture but absolutely full of cream in taste. It’s like the east and west came together and resolved their differences

beers.name: Pirate life espresso martini nitro stout
beers.desc: Amazingly creamy, rich coffee flavour and a lot of sweetness

beers.name: Sunday road the holidays
beers.desc: One of the darkest and most full flavoured lagers I’ve had. It’s too strong on the coffee for me and that’s dominating all the other flavours. Keep in mind that I'm not a coffee drinker

beers.name: Sauce pineapple squeak
beers.desc: Damn they crammed a lot of pineapple in this without it becoming tangy or harsh. Fantastic down to the last drop

beers.name: Jetty road mochachino stout
beers.desc: A coffee beer I can get much more behind. The coffee is there but the stout flavours come through stronger and balance it out. Very rich and creamy

beers.name: The mill solitary bliss
beers.desc: Good heavy west coast IIPA. Pretty easy drinking despite the strength

beers.name: Blackmans needs more cascade
beers.desc: A heavy dose of hops strong on the citrus. Has a nice little tang at the end that makes you want to come back for another sip.A good old school IPA

beers.name: Tallboy and moose highly illogical DIPA
beers.desc: Kind of strange mix of hops, there’s a juicy flavour coming through with a bit of an orange taste but also some more earthy hops. It gets better the more you drink as the juicy flavours become more prominent

beers.name: Frenchies soft tropical mist
beers.desc: Has a good level of flavour for a mid strength but light enough that you could still easily keep knocking these back. Zesty on the nose with a little citrus tang on the tongue

beers.name: Thunder road mandarin oat cream IPA
beers.desc: This is the second mandarin and cream beer I’ve had. It sounds awful but somehow keeps working perfectly, the 2 flavours complement each other and the rest of the beer

beers.name: Sierra Nevada hoppy anniversary ale
beers.desc: Heavy hoppy ale, kind of a level between regular and the torpedo. Food somehow enhances the hops

beers.name: Zytho white stout
beers.desc: Malty to the point where it actually tastes like a vanilla malt shake. Love this interesting take on a stout. Wish I had a glass for this

beers.name: White rabbit sour red
beers.desc: Red and sour seem to go well together

beers.name: Brouhaha hinterland XPA
beers.desc: Fairly standard XPA, a little more restrained than the Balter. It’s good, but not exciting

beers.name: Panhead pep torque
beers.desc: Probably the first time I’ve liked watermelon in a beer

beers.name: Deeds primal horde
beers.desc: Creamy and citrusy, a great combination

beers.name: Lab ouroboros
beers.desc: I was hoping for a bitter red ale but this is a Flemish red ale so actually more of a sour. Not a style I see very often, very refreshing

beers.name: All inn what’s up my grinches
beers.desc: Very light on the vanilla but otherwise a good stout. There is a bit of sweetness which probably goes against the name. One of those beers that gets better thee more you drink

beers.name: Alesmith IPA
beers.desc: Strong IPA with lots of rich flavours. Proper west coast IPA with nothing floral or citrusy. Enough alcohol to warm the body

beers.name: Ballistic IPA
beers.desc: Middle of the road IPA

beers.name: Prancing pony the piper
beers.desc: Slightly tropical west coast IPA. Pretty easy drinking

beers.name: Collective arts life in the clouds
beers.desc: Very smooth hazy IPA. Not sure if this beer has been through the wars hence the particulate haze, but still tastes good

beers.name: Reckless pale ale
beers.desc: Very solid pale ale, the kind of beer you would just keep drinking

beers.name: Ballistic mele kalikimaka
beers.desc: Super smooth and pineapplly. Great hazy IPA

beers.name: Frenchies summer XPA
beers.desc: Frenchies really does a good job of making light hazy beers

beers.name: Thunder road exotica 4
beers.desc: There’s something off about this.  Maybe I just had too many beers by this point

beers.name: Hop nation humbug
beers.desc: Strong stout flavours and a fair amount of bitterness but somehow smells sweet. It all manages to fit together

beers.name: Two birds total eclipse of the hop
beers.desc: Quite hoppy to start but then manages to mild out. Pretty on point for an XPA. It’s a good XPA, but there’s better ones around

beers.name: Revel mountain IPA
beers.desc: Tastes a lot lighter than most IPA. Very smashable

beers.name: Bridge roads fat man red suit fat sack
beers.desc: Super heavy in both hops and malt. Very rich and Christmasy, but I wouldn’t more than a middy

beers.name: Killer sprocket American stout
beers.desc: Fairly standard stout

beers.name: Wayward I’ll be bock
beers.desc: It’s a strange mix, dark but not a stout and malty but not to the point of a red and then quite bitter but not as much as an IPA

beers.name: Nomad Rudolphs little helper
beers.desc: It’s trying to be both full of tropical hops and amber malts at the same time, they tend to fight each other a bit to come to the front. Each flavour tends to come to the front on alternate sips . But overall it is a pretty good amber ale, and nice to see something different

beers.name: Hawthorn unicorn
beers.desc: Solid middle of the road NEIPA. I just got it for the silly picture but it turned out really good, was the best beer I found that night

beers.name: Willie the boatman no way Jose
beers.desc: A little harsh on the stomach

beers.name: Bridge road magical Christmas unicorn
beers.desc: Super creamy but with a mild taste

beers.name: Yulli’s Eugene
beers.desc: Decent lager, a nice break after a week of heavy beers

beers.name: Revel American brown ale
beers.desc: Nice sweet, slightly nutty brown ale

beers.name: Black hops eggnog stout
beers.desc: It’s like a spiced stout. A tad of ginger and something else from Christmas

beers.name: Grifter voodoo paradise
beers.desc: Super creamy nitro stout

beers.name: Boatrocker life
beers.desc: All sorts of strange. Usually barley wines are very sweet but this has a tang to it. Perhaps it was a little cold when I started drinking, as it warmed the sweetness came through more but without getting sickly. One of the nicer barley wines I’ve had

beers.name: 10 toes black
beers.desc: Has a lot of tropical flavours for a mid strength

beers.name: Akasha talus
beers.desc: Similar to other IPAs from Akasha but with a little something extra that I can’t pick. Whatever it is, it’s delicious

beers.name: 10 toes clockwork apricot
beers.desc: Super mild double IPA, to the point where you wouldn’t hesitate to have quite a few. Takes a while to get the apricot to come through which I think is what mellows it out

beers.name: White bay dreaming
beers.desc: Fairly classical Belgian wit beer. A little yeasty, but not really that exciting. Lots of better options around

beers.name: 10 toes pipeline pale ale
beers.desc: Very light refreshing pale ale. Just a hint of tropical hops

beers.name: Red right hand red IPA
beers.desc: Rich caramel flavours but not much in the way of hops but has a little bitterness

beers.name: Slipstream big billy
beers.desc: It’s a pale ale with a little extra kick. The tropical hops come off with a little tangerine tang. All fits together really well

beers.name: One drop toasted coconut pineapple nitro milkshake IPA
beers.desc: The nitro pour instructions didn’t work too well but it is very smooth. Smells like a Pina colada with lots of coconut coming through and then the pineapple comes through more in the taste. Surprisingly easy to drink given all the things going on in this beer, sadly it’s a once off beer because I could go for some more of these. I really like the way one drop do milkshake IPAs

beers.name: Bloke lager
beers.desc: I like the can design but the beer itself is very boring. Just your regular dry lager

beers.name: Blasta unbridled unicorn
beers.desc: Classical west coast IIPA which gives a nice kick in the face. Leaves a lot of fruity hops on the tip of the tongue along with a hit of bitterness

beers.name: One drop three cubed
beers.desc: Great west coast IPA without any fruity or tropical hops but lots of caramel and bitterness. It’s very smooth for the amount of flavour. I do love a good old school IPA

beers.name: Little bang face inverter
beers.desc: Some people like a little bit of lemon in their beer, this is like someone put a little bit of beer in a glass of lemon. As a beer lover, it’s not really to my taste

beers.name: Urbanaut beer blender coconut. Hazy + pineapple sour
beers.desc: Interesting concept, it’s sold as 2 cans joined together designed to be mixed together. The hazy IPA was nice but the sour was a bit too much. Together they mellow each other out, the super sour smell is still there but not as much in the taste. It comes out a little more orangey than I would expect. It’s a fun novelty, but not enough to make me choose it over a standard beer

beers.name: Holgate twin suns XPA
beers.desc: Different from most XPAs out there, a little bit punchier and a more piney choice of hops

beers.name: Devils hollow flash Kate
beers.desc: It’s an ok IPA but doesn’t really have a lot of hops coming through

beers.name: Stubbie
beers.desc: Fairly harsh bitterness without much flavour. Mostly having this as a break between stronger beers

beers.name: White bay union
beers.desc: Very crisp lager, nice to see something not going either malty or dry

beers.name: Philter IIPA
beers.desc: Slightly dank but well rounded. Very nice IPA

beers.name: Kereru resonator
beers.desc: Quite a harsh bitterness, ok but no more

beers.name: Tallboy and moose 2 solid 2 gold
beers.desc: Seems like it has gone past the best before. Harsh bitterness without much else

beers.name: Frenchies tropical brut IPA
beers.desc: Very tropical and refreshing. A little bit of pineapple but not enough to be harsh. Full of flavour but easy to drink

beers.name: Black hops G.O.A.T
beers.desc: Mild hazy IPA. Hard to really pick any specific flavours. One of those tasty yet kind of boring beers

beers.name: Grassy knoll valley lager
beers.desc: Quite a light lager with a very mild fruity tang. A good start to the drinking day and a nice beer for by the pool

beers.name: Ballistic water me lawn
beers.desc: Hits the mark for a gose of being salty and mildly sour. Very little head and a slightly hazy yellow colour. Watermelon comes through very mild in both smell and taste

beers.name: Blackflag tropical pale ale
beers.desc: Nice tropical pale ale, but nothing that exciting

beers.name: Ocean reach tropical XPA
beers.desc: Nice clear XPA with a good head. A bit more bland than the label suggests, just doesn’t have much in the way of tropical flavours

beers.name: Monteith’s Phoenix IPA
beers.desc: Pleasantly surprised with this, no big flavours but a solid strong bitterness that you would expect from an IPA

beers.name: Garage project white chocolate beer
beers.desc: The nitro makes this really creamy and the white chocolate comes through. After that the raspberry is there but still enough like a beer to keep me happy

beers.name: Old wives ale I can has IBU
beers.desc: Pretty high on the IBU as advertised, not much else going on. It's very rich

beers.name: Brick lane Revolver
beers.desc: Not getting much hoppiness, but a lot of maltyness from the dark grain. Takes a while to get acclimated to and even then it’s not exciting me

beers.name: Bridge road fruit salad sour
beers.desc: Does taste quite a lot like a fruit salad. Lots of pineapple but it’s a little artificial. Delivers on what it says

beers.name: Hope lager
beers.desc: Like a really dry Australian lager but with a little metallic zing. I think this might have been in the can too long because the taste and the smell just don’t seem right. Once the head died the bad flavours went away a little, but there wasn’t much left then

beers.name: Hop nation coffee pastry stout
beers.desc: Smells of coffee but tastes more of chocolate and pastry

beers.name: Obrien pale ale
beers.desc: There’s nothing crazy about this beer, but it’s quite refined and very easy drinking

beers.name: Hughie
beers.desc: Slightly malty lager

beers.name: Chur road Conan
beers.desc: Does have a good bit of orange coming through. Pretty nice IPA that isn’t too heavy to have more of

beers.name: Hawkers knafeh habibi
beers.desc: A very cake like stout. I do like how they have mixed pastry and beer. Hard to pick individual flavours but I do like it

beers.name: Deep creek hoppy McHop face
beers.desc: Not as heavy on the hops as I would expect, more of a smooth west coast IPA. As it warms the hop oils come through more strongly but it still seems milder than you would expect. If you’re new to DIPAs then this is for you

beers.name: Young Henry’s passionfruit and guava sour
beers.desc: Smells a little strange, mild sourness. Lives somewhere between a beer and a cider

beers.name: Frenchies pilsner
beers.desc: Decent pilsner, not too malty. Matches well with dumplings

beers.name: Stomping ground Gipps St
beers.desc: Quite a lot of dank hops on the nose for a pale ale but that’s not a complaint in any way.  Still easy drinking enough and very enjoyable

beers.name: West city NEIPA
beers.desc: Has a juicy taste but it’s undercut by a harshness that kind of ruins it. By the end I’m ok with it, but it’s not one to look for

beers.name: Bira 91 blonde
beers.desc: Malty lager, probably too heavy on the malt

beers.name: Sauce double infrared
beers.desc: That little bit of rye makes this an amazing red ale. Rich, bitter and beautiful

beers.name: Bondi draught
beers.desc: Fairly light lager. Easy drinking

beers.name: Garage project trip hop
beers.desc: With the lower alcohol percentage the rich flavours you would expect from a triple hop don’t come through, but perhaps that’s the point. The flavours don’t build up and slow down the drinking. Not my style because I’m ok with heavier beers but has nice flavours

beers.name: Revision IPA
beers.desc: Very nicely rounded, good depth of hops that leaves a little tingle on the tongue. Can’t really fault this, nothing crazy going on, just a tasty, easy drinking IPA

beers.name: John Boston the end island IPA
beers.desc: Very mild for an IPA but actually pretty nice. Easy drinking with very little heavy hops

beers.name: Big shed erebus
beers.desc: Lots of coffee in the smell but less in the taste. Very thick and heavy with a little bit of tang that somehow just dissolves leaving nothing but happiness

beers.name: Sydney hylander session IPA
beers.desc: Light beer but with a little extra bit of hops. Pretty high in ABV for a session ale which I personally like

beers.name: Rodenbach Alexander
beers.desc: Tastes a lot of sour cherries but mixed in with beer. Very different but I like it

beers.name: Sydney Potts point porter
beers.desc: Pretty on point porter. It’s much thinner than the stouts out there. There’s a little bit of coffee but it’s very mild. A good refreshing dark beer

beers.name: Cattle yard summer red
beers.desc: Kind of sweet red ale. Very light as well which makes it easy to drink. Good choice if starting out with red ales

beers.name: Black hops Neverland
beers.desc: Absolutely amazing. I don’t know how grapefruit comes out creamy instead of bitter. The percentage is so small on the can I didn’t even know it was this strong until I was half way through. Smells a little fruity and sweet but tastes much more mellow. Made me sad when the glass ran out

beers.name: Bad shepherd break yo fast
beers.desc: Smells a bit like maple but the general beer smell covers it a bit but fades . It initially tastes very smokey but that subsides and a lot of the sweetness comes through

beers.name: Thunder road Margarita Gose
beers.desc: It does have that lime and tequila taste that you get with a margarita in the taste but it smells more like a beer. It’s the kind of sour I like where it uses the sourness to pull flavours from other things into a normal light beer. It’s very easy to drink but it’s not the kind of beer that makes me want more

beers.name: Bentspoke sprocket
beers.desc: Middle of the road IPA. Good for both a bit of flavour and for having a few of them

beers.name: Mountain culture scenic route
beers.desc: Very hazy for a session IPA. Smells very tropical. It’s got some juicy flavours but also a little harshness in the finish which does diminish towards the end of the glass

beers.name: Mountain culture lager
beers.desc: Not that much to say about lagers. It’s clean and crisp

beers.name: 3 ravens shake
beers.desc: It’s all sorts of salted caramel mixed with beer

beers.name: Mountain culture moon dust stout
beers.desc: Nice thick stout. Pretty much the perfect example of what a standard stout should be

beers.name: Sierra Nevada calafornia IPA
beers.desc: Very light for an IPA but nice and tropical. Does not do well after it warms up, comes across like a bad lager

beers.name: Mountain culture laser quest
beers.desc: Looks sweet, but it’s just sour, but really only mildly. Goes down almost like water after a while. Great neutral beer to cleanse the palette

beers.name: Black hops east coast low
beers.desc: Easy drinking tropical pale ale. Light, refreshing and tasty

beers.name: Mountain culture cult juice
beers.desc: Great hazy beer. Super tropical and juicy, full of flavour. Absolutely delicious

beers.name: Range informal disco
beers.desc: Nice juicy hazy IPA, a little bit of pineapple and peach. By itself it’s very smooth but with food it’s a little too bitter. Overall very nice

beers.name: Willie the boatman tempe tim
beers.desc: Very mild pale but very good for an easy drinking mid strength

beers.name: Tallboy and moose deadset lager
beers.desc: Pretty good lager with a bit of sweetness and a fresh finish

beers.name: Garage project fuck yeah 2021
beers.desc: Very juicy without any harshness at all. Great from the first sip to the last

beers.name: bracket only one night
beers.desc: I could drink this all day despite how strong it is

beers.name: Mountain goat botanical IPA
beers.desc: It’s like a gin and tonic but in beer form

beers.name: For the road park draught
beers.desc: Little bit of sweetness but not any maltiness. A little bit harsh towards the end. But overall very easy drinking without much flavour

beers.name: White rabbit golden sour
beers.desc: Very mild sour. Easy drinking

beers.name: Two birds chew tang clan
beers.desc: Golden orange colour with a slightly yeasty aroma and a hint of cloves. Has the little tang in the taste that the name promises

beers.name: Hop nation Melbourne fog
beers.desc: Looks very juicy but mostly just tastes bitter. Gets a little better as it goes but overall pretty disappointing

beers.name: Otherside headliner
beers.desc: Heavy bitterness to start but that gets replaced with a strange flavour and almost a tang of chilli in the end. A very strange beer, and a little bit heavy on sediment

beers.name: Garage project golden path
beers.desc: Another winner from garage project. Even with a low alcohol content it packs in flavour. Lots of pine aroma and citrus fruits in the taste. A good beer that you could have a great many of

beers.name: Little bang 50 dalrymples
beers.desc: Has a lot of pine coming through from the hops but it tastes very fresh. A strong beer to savour and enjoy

beers.name: Nomad mango oat cream DDH IPA
beers.desc: Looks very juicy. Has aA fair chunk of mango flavour but it’s a little bit overshadowed by the acid that comes through with the orange. As the beer warms it becomes much better and hits that juicy target in both smell and taste

beers.name: Sailors grave lager lager lager pils
beers.desc: Nice golden colour. There’s a really nice malty sweetness in this which is unfortunately overshadowed by a metallic taste. Smells like a cheap Aussie lager. Some good things here but just misses the mark

beers.name: Bunnley Vienna lager
beers.desc: Very dry with a harsh bitterness. Really not great

beers.name: Yullis brews Toby’s crossing
beers.desc: Very creamy IPA even though it doesn’t look it. Almost seems like some mandarin is in there. Good balance of flavour and easy drinking

beers.name: Modus operandi allures
beers.desc: Another beer that looks like a pale ale and tastes like a coffee. I’m not sure if I’m getting used to the style or if this one is just a little less heavy on the coffee but I’m ok with this one

beers.name: Bridge road nitro robust porter
beers.desc: Very thin for a dark beer, the nitro doesn’t hold very well at all. Kind of boring, goes down easy

beers.name: Akasha basil smash
beers.desc: Getting more ginger than basil but it works. Very smooth and a little creamy. Great down to the last drop

beers.name: White bay heaps deep
beers.desc: Good west coast IPA. It’s a little dank but not too heavy with a little floral sweetness on the tip of the tongue. Goes down a little too easy given the ABV

beers.name: Bright hype boi oat cream NEIPA
beers.desc: Delicious looking hazy beer but sadly tastes worse than it looks. Has some acidity that takes away from the juiciness

beers.name: Bridge road NEed
beers.desc: Heavy bitterness and some acidity. Not much else

beers.name: Pirate life tea & biccies
beers.desc: Doesn’t seem much like tea, a little too bitter though I didn’t add sugar or milk. I can understand what it’s going for but it needs that extra sweetness to hit it

beers.name: Chur straya! hazy IPA
beers.desc: Beautiful hazy complexion, smells a little bit sour but fairly plain. But it tastes like a summer fruit salad, mostly pineapple. Not. Sure why this is made by a kiwi brewery, but it’s good

beers.name: Clown shoes zen garden
beers.desc: I was expecting big hoppy flavour hits but instead it’s more like a subdued west coast IPA

beers.name: Coastal myall marzen
beers.desc: Slightly tangy and a little malty. Very easy drinking

beers.name: Two birds rice rice baby
beers.desc: Quite an interesting mix of flavours. Almost like a really mild sour sauce but with a little herbal tang

beers.name: Rogue Batsquatch
beers.desc: It’s got a good haze. I wonder if I’ve had so many strong IPAs that this thing tastes mild. Good flavour, just expected it to be stronger

beers.name: Quakers nectaron
beers.desc: Slightly tangy pale ale. Not too heavy on the hops but flavours slowly come out over time

beers.name: Black hops tropic like it’s hot
beers.desc: Quite strong on ginger but not quite as much as a normal ginger beer. The lemongrass adds a nice extra bit

beers.name: Firedoor ember ale
beers.desc: Looks delicious but doesn’t really have much to it

beers.name: Mountain goat Newtonian
beers.desc: Quite light with a little fruity kick

beers.name: Mountain goat IPA
beers.desc: Nice west coast IPA with a little extra floral kick and a finish of earthy notes. Very nice

beers.name: Hope super super juicy
beers.desc: Seems more on the west coast heavy mellow IPA than a NEIPA. But who cares, it’s delicious. Huge amount of alcohol that you could easily miss

beers.name: New England raindrop IPA
beers.desc: Nice mild IPA, seemed really great to start but then kind of died off

beers.name: James squire talisman
beers.desc: Rich and malty but not heavy on hops

beers.name: Ballistic Sleep when you’re dead west coast IPA
beers.desc: Straight up dank IPA. Just what I was feeling like

beers.name: Pirate life ants in ya pants
beers.desc: Looks a little green, but just tastes like a pale ale. There is a little tang to it

beers.name: Big shed pilsner
beers.desc: Nice golden colour with slight notes of pepper and a dry finish

beers.name: Frenchies Kamchatka
beers.desc: Rich and earthy. A nice solid very dark stout

beers.name: Mountain goat botanical IPA
beers.desc: This beer is just amazing, it has all the good parts of an IPA and gin mixed together. Despite how that may sound it works perfectly

beers.name: Deeds fiscal damage
beers.desc: Looks super juicy and smells exactly like it looks. Lots of orange and citrus. There’s a little bit extra sourness that masks some of the fruity flavours. Enough booze to warm you up

beers.name: Hawkers into the forest I go
beers.desc: Wasn’t expecting something so pink. But it’s a good sour, not too much or too sweet

beers.name: Sauce Caribbean fog
beers.desc: So so good. Light on the stomach but with lots of hops in the mouth

beers.name: Clown shoes undead party crasher
beers.desc: A little bit of tang in a stout that is milder than it looks

beers.name: Ballistic grandfather oaked ale
beers.desc: Beautiful dark amber colour. Rich taste with a bit of tang,  little bit of sweetness. Very little on the hop side and one for savouring over a long time

beers.name: Feral shooters juicy IPA
beers.desc: Delivers a good juice hit in a hazy IPA. A little acidic to start but bellows quickly

beers.name: Modus operandi wax flower sour
beers.desc: No idea what a wax flower is, though there is a slight waxy mouthfeel which is strange for a sour. It’s a bit different from your regular sour but not by a lot

beers.name: Akasha endless haze
beers.desc: Good hazy pale ale. Lots of flavour, not much booze

beers.name: Modern times hazy citrus DIPA
beers.desc: Very mild for a double IPA and a little creamy. Good for either smashing or sipping

beers.name: Alesmith tiki IPA
beers.desc: Nice tropical IPA. There’s a little bit of coconut coming through which at first made me think it was cashmere hops. A lot of particulate haze which might be from the travel

beers.name: Sydney brewery east coast IPA
beers.desc: Middle of the road IPA. Kind of like a pale ale with a little extra hops

beers.name: Sydney brewery double red IPA
beers.desc: Kind of mixed up with flavours

beers.name: Sydney brewery black IPA
beers.desc: Not much of an IPA. Really just malty

beers.name: Newstead windmill
beers.desc: Delivers on being a dry stout, which is a little strange. Not really a combination for me

beers.name: One drop dark lager
beers.desc: Good mix of a little extra malt and still being light and easy to drink. It’s almost on the side of a brown ale in flavour

beers.name: Deeds dkat Amarillo
beers.desc: Strong hoppy tang with a heavy bunch of hops

beers.name: Sunday road cryotherapy
beers.desc: Nice syrupy beer without any bitterness

beers.name: Atomic T-Wrecked
beers.desc: Very smooth IPA, has that kind of botanical flavour that I love

beers.name: Deep creek monsoon
beers.desc: Deep dank hops in this one. Pretty easy drinking even though it’s quite strong. Feels like there’s some depth missing

beers.name: New England grandad brown
beers.desc: Nice sweet brown alee

beers.name: Hop nation rattenhund
beers.desc: Tastes like a cheap pilsner from Eastern Europe. Hits the style well, but not to my liking

beers.name: Bracket SFO
beers.desc: Strange mix of hops, but delicious

beers.name: Bracket red IPA
beers.desc: Solid mix of bitterness and a little bit of hops

beers.name: Garage project bug powder dust
beers.desc: A little bit of pineapple notes

beers.name: Hop nation Santa Fe
beers.desc: Nice bit of orange and pineapple. Lighter than it looks, could easily have a few

beers.name: Hope salted caramel hazy IIIPA
beers.desc: Not as bitter as I expected which really lets the salted caramel come through but without being sickly sweet

beers.name: Mountain culture flavour generator
beers.desc: Very fresh and quite thick but not too milky, more on the tart side

beers.name: Ballistic Mexican hot chocolate stout
beers.desc: Just a little tang of chilli that slowly builds up. Outside of the chilli it’s quite a mild stout with a little bit of coffee on the nose. Can’t drink it quickly though

beers.name: Philter saison
beers.desc: Classic saison with just a little bit of banana

beers.name: Green beacon fathom saison
beers.desc: It’s all about the fresh pear in this one.  Very different saison form my last one

beers.name: Panhead lug nut
beers.desc: English ale without much going on. Seems like they added biscuits to make it more interesting but it’s not enough

beers.name: Basement Brewhouse Daaarryl, Daaarryl!
beers.desc: Ok to start with but quickly overwhelming

beers.name: White rabbit chocolate stout
beers.desc: Pretty much like the dark ale

beers.name: Mildura XPA
beers.desc: Very yeasty and with a very coarse carbonation. Has a lot of the flavours that I don’t want in my home brew. Just too yeasty

beers.name: Gage roads Sidetrack XPA
beers.desc: Pretty mild but a good flavour

beers.name: Mildura IPA
beers.desc: Bottle says IPA, but this is a flat brown ale. It’s not an awful flavour, but there’s no hops

beers.name: 2 halfs brown porter nitro
beers.desc: Very easy drinking brown ale. Not a lot to it, but very refined

beers.name: 2 halfs Keller pils
beers.desc: A pilsner with a little bit of sour. Not really for me 5.5/

beers.name: 2 halfs liquid baguette
beers.desc: Kind of an oily film which makes it rich. Pretty nice though

beers.name: 2 halfs centennial pale
beers.desc: Kind of bitter pale ale. Not that exciting

beers.name: Mildura APA
beers.desc: Another strangely tangy beer without much in the way of hops. No good

beers.name: Philter old ale
beers.desc: A lot like the classic Tooheys old

beers.name: Mildura Margarita Gose
beers.desc: Absolutely no fizz, smells a little mouldy but tastes vaguely like a margarita. Not as bad as I expected

beers.name: 2 halfs trident pale
beers.desc: Very nice slightly bitter pale ale

beers.name: Philter hazy pale
beers.desc: Nice haze, lots of floral and slightly citrus smells but with a pretty light taste

beers.name: Pirate life NEIPA cryo
beers.desc: Very smooth IPA, absolutely smashable

beers.name: Swan draught
beers.desc: Quite malty but not too bitter. Kind of like a pilsner

beers.name: Yullis papaya pale
beers.desc: Pretty good pale ale with some richer flavours match the darker colour. Almost comes across as mandarin

beers.name: Yullis uncle Gus
beers.desc: The lime adds a nice extra dimension to pilsner, a good session bev

beers.name: Stone and wood Tequila queen
beers.desc: Not too heavy on the sour but the tequila comes through quite a lot with a little lime. Quite good and better as it goes along

beers.name: Willie the boatman crying heidi
beers.desc: Has that smooth cashmere feel but there’s a strange taste, a little overly yeasty and never quite comes together

beers.name: Mildura brewing pilsner
beers.desc: Another beer with very little fizz and too much yeast. Tastes nothing like a pilsner, more like a cider

beers.name: Bracket BOS NEIPA
beers.desc: Absolutely delicious from the first sip. Very low bitterness and a great haze. Exactly what you expect from a NEIPA

beers.name: Bracket citra haze
beers.desc: Has a lot of creamyness coming through for a citra single hop. Light for what it is but still high on the flavour side

beers.name: Bracket Mosaic haze
beers.desc: Another creamy and hoppy beer. Very rounded taste which leaves very little afterwards

beers.name: Atomic Vienna dreamin
beers.desc: Highly malty lager. It’s ok for a lager

beers.name: Atomic brown ale
beers.desc: Fairly standard brown, easy drinking

beers.name: Mountain culture harry DIPA
beers.desc: Super mellow NEIPA

beers.name: Batch huge Kahuna imperial brown ale
beers.desc: There’s a super familiar sweet tastes the edge of this one. A little bit of caramel, with a slightly burnt addition

beers.name: Frenchies hazy IPA
beers.desc: Tastes a bit of Apricot. Very nice and I could go for another

beers.name: Yoyogi gin IPA
beers.desc: Not very exciting, a fairly plain west coast IPA. There’s a very subtle gin flavour in there but you really have to search for it

beers.name: Yoyogi honey cream ale
beers.desc: Lots of honey coming through, not much cream

beers.name: Wayward sourade blue blast berry gose
beers.desc: Kind of like a blue Powerade mixed with beer. Smells weird and takes a while to get used to. Overall it’s a mixed bag, but ok

beers.name: Wayward island life
beers.desc: Has a strange smell that I can’t quite pick. Quite rounded in the malt but never quite works

beers.name: Moondog all killer no filler
beers.desc: Immediately has some vanilla coming through, especially in the smell, more than I would have expected. Behind that it’s got a good creamy mouthfeel. Easy drinking with lots of flavours

beers.name: Stone and wood east point
beers.desc: Quite similar to the pacific ale but maybe a little bit more tangy. Gets a little bit sickly over time. Pretty bad for something so weak

beers.name: Nomad brookie draught
beers.desc: Quite a malty lager. Really not that great

beers.name: Sailors grave first harvest hayzy
beers.desc: Not exactly what you would expect from a hazy, more of a malty west coast. But it’s good so who cares

beers.name: Bentspoke bent shovel
beers.desc: Interesting malt profile. Not a lot going on but leaves a nice after taste

beers.name: Dainton vienneipa
beers.desc: Not the normal colour for a dessert beer. Has a little bit of ice cream and vanilla coming through. Interesting and also tasty

beers.name: Garage project white mischief
beers.desc: Pretty good all round sour

beers.name: Dainton equalizer
beers.desc: Finding it hard to say anything about this one. It’s quite light so not much comes through. Kind of boring

beers.name: Tiny rebel stay puft
beers.desc: Has a good taste of marshmallow in a solid porter. That little bit of extra sweetness really brings it together

beers.name: Range morning ritual
beers.desc: Very heavy

beers.name: Jindabyne redX
beers.desc: Moderate bitter red ale. Good staple for a long session

beers.name: Bunnley grapefruit IPA
beers.desc: Smells quite a bit of grapefruit. Good mix of hops and malt

beers.name: Bridge road mandarin grisette
beers.desc: Like a Belgian ale mixed with a sour

beers.name: Modus Koko black
beers.desc: Stouty and chocolaty. Maybe something that doesn’t sit right, or maybe the wrong time of night

beers.name: Tallboy and moose fun dip
beers.desc: A little bit all over the place. Slightly creamy but also tangy. Gets better as it goes down but there’s no exciting flavours that makes you want to come back

beers.name: Temple anytime pale ale
beers.desc: Slightly rough pale ale

beers.name: Batch island style coconut IPA
beers.desc: A bit too much yeast but the coconut is nice

beers.name: Brick lane stereobreaker
beers.desc: Just a little hit of rye which is balanced out with some sweetness

beers.name: Bright mystery batch-02
beers.desc: Quite yeasty, reminds me a little bit of a Belgian ale. I like the mystery element, but this seems like a beer that didn’t work

beers.name: Woolshed the big orange
beers.desc: Tastes like Fanta minus the sugar. Pretty balanced and easy drinking

beers.name: Revel hopbro superchoice
beers.desc: Has a bit too much fizz, kind of a Belgian head. A bit of a strange taste, the whole thing reminding me of a Belgian IPA

beers.name: Brewdog vs cloud water NEIPA
beers.desc: Pretty great from the start. Easy drinking, good level of hops, much sadness as my glass runs dry

beers.name: Hope oat cream IPA
beers.desc: On a slow ramp up of IPAs this evening and loving it. Very creamy taste with a slight zest. Delivers exactly what the can promises

beers.name: Temple New world order
beers.desc: Heavy stout, leaves a slight oiliness in the mouth

beers.name: Dainton shark punch nado
beers.desc: Strange set of hops but the consistency doesn’t let it linger. Not as punchy as the label might indicate and much more on the IPA side. Pretty good all round

beers.name: Fonzie abbott twin palms
beers.desc: Quite a bitter pale ale

beers.name: Green beacon ditch hopper
beers.desc: Seems a bit like a pilsner. It’s a pretty good beer but not my cup of tea

beers.name: Badlands fashion NEIPA
beers.desc: I gave badlands another shot and once again I’ve been let down. There’s a slight mouldy sourness like this beer has gone bad

beers.name: Green beacon grappler lager
beers.desc: Smells like a pilsner but tastes very dry and crisp

beers.name: Slipstream scooter
beers.desc: Good light red ale. A little bit on the fizzy side

beers.name: Deeds one standard drink
beers.desc: It’s pretty good for a weak beer, but plenty of tastier beers out there

beers.name: Dainton Bright-er daze
beers.desc: Very nice

beers.name: Urban alley long beach creamsicle
beers.desc: Nice hazy IPA. Easy enough drinking

beers.name: Your mates sally
beers.desc: Too fizzy and a bit of a yeasty Belgian taste

beers.name: Sea legs tropical lager
beers.desc: Not that tropical, more on the crisp side. Would go down a treat on a beach. Maybe not terribly exciting, but quite well made

beers.name: Batch don’t judge a beer by it’s colour
beers.desc: Another heavy coffee beer with a light colour. But this one isn’t hitting me as hard and gets better the more I drink

beers.name: Big shed boozy fruit
beers.desc: Exactly what the label says, like a bowl of fruit punch with the perfect level of beeryness

beers.name: Cooks river amber ale
beers.desc: Hits a bit heavy to start but rounds out

beers.name: Local runaway IPA
beers.desc: Mellow hops making an easy to drink IPA
