beers.name: Foghorn king street pale
beers.desc: Really interesting hops. Smooth and cashmere like

beers.name: Ocean reach Strawberry gose
beers.desc: Very subtle strawberry flavour in a fairly plain sour. Quite easy drinking

beers.name: Dunbar EPA
beers.desc: Quite a nice malty pale ale

beers.name: Range mustard
beers.desc: Really nice Munich style lager. Reminds me of Oktoberfest. Good level of malt but still crisp

beers.name: Hope sunny boy sour
beers.desc: Lots of orange but without any astringency. It’s very much like having a sunny boy but with a whole heap of alcohol

beers.name: Cattleyard cherry redhead
beers.desc: The maltiness of the red is rounded out by hazy hops. Nicely malty but easy to drink

beers.name: Working title sideways oat cream rosé XPA
beers.desc: Seems like a beer with a dash of wine. Not much in the way of hops and smells strange for a beer. Sounded really interesting but not enough going on the beer side

beers.name: Innate New England IPA
beers.desc: A little bit harsh but a very juicy beer

beers.name: Garage project red rocks
beers.desc: Nice rounded malt smell with a slight smokiness. A nice way to finish the night

beers.name: Bunnley X5 fru-its
beers.desc: Tart and refreshing and a little bit fruity

beers.name: Range the rest is noise
beers.desc: Super smooth and juicy. Just a mellow juicy beer that I want more of

beers.name: Urban alley ruby RRIPA
beers.desc: Great strong smell and an easy drinking

beers.name: Akasha mutiny on the bounty
beers.desc: Very creamy milk stout

beers.name: Range quench
beers.desc: Very light and easy to drink with a bit of sweetness. A good drink to cool down after exercise

beers.name: Coconspirators the mechanic
beers.desc: Nice hazy yellow colour to it. Very smooth drinking and a little creamy

beers.name: Hope Idaho 7
beers.desc: It’s a straight kick in thee face, very heavy taste of alcohol

beers.name: Boatrocker kokomo
beers.desc: Very sweet, reminds me of a tropical beach in winter when I’m locked inside

beers.name: Yullis dolly aldrin
beers.desc: Couldn’t taste the strawberry at all

beers.name: Single hope neipa
beers.desc: Strange hop flavours

beers.name: 3 ravens orange sherbet creamsicle
beers.desc: Tastes like creaming soda. Too much soft drink, not enough beer

beers.name: Akasha lupulin fog
beers.desc: Looks a bit better than it tastes. Kind of orangey

beers.name: Colonial IPA
beers.desc: Citrusy and tasty

beers.name: Wayward wayward son
beers.desc: Velvety smooth. Not much on the nose but just that right level of easy to drink without it being gone before you notice

beers.name: Hope grapefruit hazy IPA
beers.desc: Lots of grapefruit flavour and smell. Makes it a bit bitter but still a good IPA

beers.name: One drop mango milkshake IPA
beers.desc: Nitro pour came out really well. The mango isn’t that strong but it sits nicely with the creaminess of the nitro. Almost reminds me of a mango lassi without the sugar, though I would consider this sweet for an IPA

beers.name: Bracket birthday suit
beers.desc: Very smooth to the point of being dangerous. Mine didn’t come out as orange as I’ve seen other pours but I assume it tastes the same. I would love to have a case of these fellas. It’s one of those beers which isn’t trying to do anything crazy, just being a great mellow IPA

beers.name: Garage project yuzukossho
beers.desc: Kind of a strange mix. Not really getting any of the saltiness. Mostly just a sour

beers.name: Bright adffogato stout
beers.desc: Tastes a bit like tiramisu. Leaves a nice sweet after taste

beers.name: Nomad jetlag
beers.desc: You know when you drink that a last little bit in the can before moving to the glass. Well that first sip was sickening. Luckily what was in the glass was much better. But still overall it’s only got as much flavour as a pale ale

beers.name: Sauce strawberry dreamshake
beers.desc: Haze has gone a bit lumpy which left a lot of sediment. Smells a little sweet but isn’t as sweet in the taste. I was expecting more but it is good

beers.name: Tallboy and moose nitro milk stout
beers.desc: Pretty standard stout. A pretty good balance not being too heavy or light Ok but not exciting

beers.name: Bracket blackberry & Vanilla
beers.desc: The vanilla and blackberry come together like a dessert but still with that little bit of sourness and a little bit of beer

beers.name: Little bang chocolate stout
beers.desc: Mid level stout. Not bad, not exciting, quite mellow

beers.name: Frenchies Si Ti Va
beers.desc: There’s a little tang that takes away from the smooth IPA

beers.name: Brouhaha New England IPA
beers.desc: Nice citrusy and pineapple taste but a little harsh in the smell. Gets better as it goes down as orange comes through

beers.name: Bracket six four four
beers.desc: Surprisingly clear for the style of beer. Hops are coming through strongly. Smells quite alcoholic but doesn’t taste like it. A slow drink

beers.name: Bracket 7 Baraka
beers.desc: So much coffee, I don’t even drink coffee but I still like this

beers.name: Dainton overdrive
beers.desc: When east coast IPAs came out I was excited, now west coasts are so rare I love when I find one. Not too dank, but has some rich hops that come across a little malty

beers.name: Bracket blend
beers.desc: Almost no fizz, and very sour. Not a lot of fruit but the tang is nice. It’s a good sour but wouldn’t be the first thing I went for from bracket

beers.name: Bentspoke Desscent21
beers.desc: So incredibly dark and the alcohol comes through really strong

beers.name: Bracket IOU
beers.desc: Had a lot of yeast left in the can which tainted the taste a bit. Looks great and smells fantastic but not my favourite from bracket

beers.name: Bracket on the fence
beers.desc: Beautiful orange colouring. Maybe it’s just me coming off some light beers previously, but this is great

beers.name: Ballistic strata
beers.desc: Smells and tastes faintly of apple which is really rare, but also rare is a new west coast IPA. Great amber colour and quite a mild hop profile

beers.name: Hitachino IPA
beers.desc: Quite malty for an IPA and with a slight tinge of orange. Not a lot of hops but that’s ok

beers.name: Bracket hazy pale
beers.desc: Really like the hop mix, Amarillo gives that orange zest with some citrus from the citra. Smell is fantastic

beers.name: Bracket over the fence
beers.desc: Super mellow and hoppy. Great easy drinking hazy IPA

beers.name: Bracket daisy chained
beers.desc: Quite a tangy IPA, but delicious. I feel like I should be in a less drunk state to enjoy this

beers.name: Bracket bramble
beers.desc: Not as great as the vanilla version, but very full of fruit

beers.name: Bracket morning cuppa
beers.desc: It’s a cup of coffee more than it’s a beer. Probably a good choice for a wake up beer

beers.name: Hitachino white ale
beers.desc: The label had me expecting much more in the way of spices

beers.name: Breakfast at Stepney
beers.desc: Pretty heavy on the coffee

beers.name: Bracket Russian imperial stout
beers.desc: It’s surprisingly hard to catch the alcohol in this one, it comes through a little bit more once it warms. It’s not a beer that I would reach out for often, but for what it is it is amazing

beers.name: Hope imperial pineapple sour
beers.desc: Tastes and smells like a glass of pineapple. Quite sour, but so is the fruit

beers.name: Slow lane belgian blonde
beers.desc: Very mellow belgian ale. Good but not my favourite

beers.name: Slow lane Hefeweizen
beers.desc: Very herbal and zesty. Great with a pretzel

beers.name: Slow lane hop barn
beers.desc: Smells like farmhouse and fruits. Nothing like a regular IPA. Really complex with all sorts of flavours in here

beers.name: Slow lane simple coercion
beers.desc: Not your normal hazy. Like a pale mixed with a belgian ale

beers.name: Slow lane liquid bread
beers.desc: So very dark. Has tinges of being a sweet barleywine

beers.name: One drop double vanilla custard pancake nitro thickshake
beers.desc: Pretty much delivers everything in the name. Very sweet and very hard to taste the alcohol

beers.name: One drop forager
beers.desc: Pretty good hazy pale. Nothing really elevating it

beers.name: One drop choc vanilla porter
beers.desc: Delivers exactly what the name says. Very heavy but it’s my kind of beer

beers.name: Marsden south seas lager
beers.desc: Pretty smooth lager with a slightly malty smell

beers.name: Beatnik fudge stout
beers.desc: Doesn’t taste much like fudge but there is a little sweetness. Pretty easy drinking overall

beers.name: Pirate life Betty’s beer
beers.desc: Kind of bland. Expected more from Pirate life

beers.name: Green beacon Imperial pastry stout
beers.desc: Not as heavy on coffee as I expected. Quite rounded

beers.name: Bojak calypso hazy IPA
beers.desc: Good colour with a solid haze. Very tropical hop smells. First sips from the bottom of the can had a bit of hop burn but the rest was smooth. It’s not amazing but hits the mark

beers.name: Bojak el camino
beers.desc: Smells malty, earthy and floral. Fairly easy to drink but not exciting

beers.name: Bojak the milk man
beers.desc: Pretty harsh to start. never really rounds out

beers.name: Frenchies la grosse Lola
beers.desc: Reminds me a lot of cantillon which is not what I was expecting. Slight mustyness. Lots of sediment in the bottom. It does deliver on the apricot

beers.name: Staves lucid dream
beers.desc: Quite a strong bitterness without much flavour coming from the hops. It’s a little bit boring

beers.name: Bojak out of hand 3
beers.desc: Pretty strong flavoured pale ale yet still very drinkable

beers.name: Mountain culture wet bandits
beers.desc: Great orange and yellow hazy colouring. Mellow smell of flowers and peaches. Very easy drinking for the strength, just a little tang on the tip of the tongue

beers.name: 4 pines red XPA
beers.desc: Almost completely neutral smell but with the proper red bitterness

beers.name: Deeds lazy summer
beers.desc: A little bit too much orange which brings some harshness. It’s good to start but gets a bit much towards the end

beers.name: Mr banks throw pillow
beers.desc: Smells a lot like vanilla and tastes a little sweet. Pretty easy to drink but not exciting

beers.name: Garage project someone special
beers.desc: A hazy IPA that reminds me of old west coast IPAs but with a creamier mouthfeel. Quite high on the bitterness but there’s enough flavour in there that it doesn’t matter. I miss heavy hitting IPAs like these

beers.name: Jetty road dank and stormy
beers.desc: It’s pretty high on the bitterness but any dank hops are overwhelmed by the heavy malts. Towards the end the hops start to subtly come through. Despite the missing hops it’s still a very enjoyable beer

beers.name: Kaiju tangerine love machine
beers.desc: It’s a good level of sourness that doesn’t overwhelm it being a beer. Does remind me of a bitter citrus fruit. Very easy drinking and refreshing

beers.name: Big shed LUPOwheat
beers.desc: Has a nice velvety smooth smell, just a little dank. Quite easy drinking, there’s a bitterness there but it’s not too high. Hard to pick out any individual flavours

beers.name: Wayward dreaming of an amber Christmas
beers.desc: Almost red in colour. Very rich malty flavour that lingers at the back of the tongue. Very little in the smell apart from some malty bitterness. One of the best amber ales I’ve ever had

beers.name: Hop nation St Nick’s nightcap
beers.desc: Reminds me a lot of a standard Aussie lager. The hops haven’t added much flavour, mostly bitterness

beers.name: Ballistic it’s a cracker
beers.desc: Gorgeous orange colouring. Full on bitterness with some rich mellow undertones. A very classical west coast IPA. Despite the strong bitterness it still goes well with food

beers.name: Garage project progressive infinite iterations
beers.desc: Quite mild but with lots of flavour in there. Smells a little bit yeasty but I can’t taste it. Just keeps getting better as I drink it

beers.name: Hawkers solarism
beers.desc: Super dark but initial taste is mostly sour. Kind of like a blueberry tart. A pretty slow drink

beers.name: Fresh tracks pristine lager
beers.desc: It’s a lager with slightly less offensive bitterness

beers.name: Blackmans simcoe cryo
beers.desc: A mild and balanced pale ale. Very easy drinking

beers.name: Nomad gingerbread milk stout
beers.desc: Well it’s definitely gingery. Takes a long time to get through that into anything else. Very much like a gingerbread soaked in beer

beers.name: Mismatch XPA
beers.desc: An XPA much more on the West coast side than the East. Smell is dominated by caramel. A lot of sweetness and richness in the taste as well

beers.name: Two birds berry Christmas baby
beers.desc: So it looks nothing like a beer, but that’s ok. It’s very fruity with almost no bitterness. Luckily the salt cuts through it making it sickly without being noticeable. Really sits where I like a salted sour. The blueberry is there but not overwhelming. If you’re feeling something on the light and refreshing side, definitely worth a go

beers.name: Stone and wood jasper hoppy red ale
beers.desc: Delivers nicely on a good mouthful of hops but still with that strong red bitterness. The malt doesn’t come through as much as expected

beers.name: Foghorn withnail rye
beers.desc: A good malty rye with a heavy bitterness. Exactly what I expect from a rye ale

beers.name: Akasha Ron McClane cryo pop IPA
beers.desc: Very mellow for an IPA which helps it go down easy. The perfect session IPA but with more booze

beers.name: Modus halo hunter
beers.desc: Kind of hoppy ale with a little belgian ting. Pretty good balance between the two. The yeast comes through much more towards the end

beers.name: Slow lane stranger danger
beers.desc: Very clean and crisp

beers.name: Hargreaves hill Babooshka vanilla milk stout
beers.desc: Pretty mild milk stout. Quite creamy with a little hint of vanilla

beers.name: Slipstream grizzly
beers.desc: Interesting mix with the sweetness from a brown and the hops from an IPA

beers.name: New England wolf & fox Slovenian Hopped Pale Ale
beers.desc: Some quite tart hops which gives a little sweetness towards the end

beers.name: Yulli’s Glenn's Negroni pilsner
beers.desc: Not sure how those 2 things go together at all. It’s light like a pilsner but then has a slightly strange aftertaste like the orange zest in a negroni. Still quite crisp and refreshing

beers.name: Sunday road Yule Fuel
beers.desc: Little bit of hop burn at the end of the can. Has a lot of fruity smells coming off it. Taste is pretty good, rounded at the back of the throat and bitter and malty on the tongue. Gets better and better as I drink

beers.name: Currumbin valley local
beers.desc: Easy drinking pale ale, very light on the hops

beers.name: One drop strawberry vanilla nitro milkshake
beers.desc: A lot like strawberries and cream or marshmallows. A good dessert beer, but it does sit on that line of getting too sickly sweet

beers.name: Monty’s citra pale ale
beers.desc: Not really much of that usual citra hop coming through. Quite a low bitterness pale ale. Good for a hot day

beers.name: Monty’s Schwarzbier
beers.desc: Quite light for a dark beer. Reminds me of a tooheys old. Still easy drinking in the heat

beers.name: Boatrocker triple
beers.desc: A pretty perfect belgian triple. It’s like I expect the alcohol to come through but it never does

beers.name: Currumbin valley lazy hazy
beers.desc: Good all round pale ale. Nice amount of hops

beers.name: Currumbin valley waste oil
beers.desc: Very heavy stout with a lot of chocolate coming through from the roasted grains

beers.name: Sauce stoutmas
beers.desc: It’s a bit too much coffee for me. Dark and thick and goes down surprisingly easy

beers.name: Helios cyclops IPA
beers.desc: Kind of earthy and sweet. Only bitter on the tip of the tongue

beers.name: Black hops hop swap hazy IPA
beers.desc: Has a little bit of hop burn at the bottom but it’s juicy at the top

beers.name: 4 brothers arrogant brother
beers.desc: Fairly light smokeyness. There’s a bit of a tang that kind of gets in the way. Pretty good

beers.name: 4 brothers Oktoberfest marzen
beers.desc: Very mellow. Like a lager but with a bit more depth in the malt and less harsh bitterness. Has a very faint hint of spices

beers.name: Anderson valley Barney flats Oatmeal stout
beers.desc: Surprisingly tart for a stout. Otherwise it’s a pretty mild stout. It’s not trying to be anything but a good stout
